05
05Dt 1:1 These are the words Moses spoke to all Israel across the Jordan in the wilderness, in the Arabah opposite Suph, between Paran and Tophel, Laban, Hazeroth, and Di-zahab.
05Dt 1:2 It is an eleven-day journey from Horeb to Kadesh-barnea by way of Mount Seir.
05Dt 1:3 In the fortieth year, in the eleventh month, on the first of the month, Moses told the Israelites everything the LORD had commanded him [to say] to them.
05Dt 1:4 This was after he had defeated Sihon king of the Amorites, who lived in Heshbon, and Og king of Bashan, who lived in Ashtaroth, at Edrei.
05Dt 1:5 Across the Jordan in the land of Moab, Moses began to explain this law, saying:
05Dt 1:6 "The LORD our God spoke to us at Horeb, 'You have stayed at this mountain long enough.
05Dt 1:7 Resume your journey and go to the hill country of the Amorites and their neighbors in the Arabah, the hill country, the lowlands, the Negev and the sea coast-- to the land of the Canaanites and to Lebanon as far as the Euphrates River.
05Dt 1:8 See, I have set the land before you. Enter and take possession of the land the LORD swore to give to your fathers Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob and their descendants after them.'
05Dt 1:9 "I said to you at that time: I can't bear [the responsibility for] you on my own.
05Dt 1:10 The LORD your God has so multiplied you that today you are as numerous as the stars of the sky.
05Dt 1:11 May the LORD, the God of your fathers, increase you a thousand times more, and bless you as He promised you.
05Dt 1:12 But how can I bear your troubles, burdens, and disputes by myself?
05Dt 1:13 Appoint for yourselves wise, understanding, and respected men from each of your tribes, and I will make them your leaders.
05Dt 1:14 "You replied to me, 'What you propose to do is good.'
05Dt 1:15 "So I took the leaders of your tribes, wise and respected men, and set them over you as leaders: officials for thousands, hundreds, fifties, and tens, and officers for your tribes.
05Dt 1:16 I commanded your judges at that time: Hear [the cases] between your brothers, and judge rightly between a man and his brother or a foreign resident.
05Dt 1:17 Do not show partiality when rendering judgment; listen to small and great alike. Do not be intimidated by anyone, for judgment belongs to God. Bring me any case too difficult for you, and I will hear it.
05Dt 1:18 At that time I commanded you about all the things you were to do.
05Dt 1:19 "We then set out from Horeb and went across all the great and terrible wilderness you saw on the way to the hill country of the Amorites, just as the LORD our God had commanded us. When we reached Kadesh-barnea,
05Dt 1:20 I said to you: You have reached the hill country of the Amorites, which the LORD our God is giving us.
05Dt 1:21 See, the LORD your God has set the land before you. Go up and take possession of it as the LORD, the God of your fathers, has told you. Do not be afraid or discouraged.
05Dt 1:22 "Then all of you approached me and said, 'Let's send men ahead of us, so that they may explore the land for us and bring us back a report about the route we should go up and the cities we will come to.'
05Dt 1:23 The plan seemed good to me, so I selected 12 men from among you, one man for each tribe.
05Dt 1:24 They left and went up into the hill country and came to the Valley of Eshcol, scouting the land.
05Dt 1:25 They took some of the fruit from the land in their hands, carried [it] down to us, and brought us back a report: 'The land the LORD our God is giving us is good.'
05Dt 1:26 "But you were not willing to go up, rebelling against the command of the LORD your God.
05Dt 1:27 You grumbled in your tents and said, 'The LORD brought us out of the land of Egypt to deliver us into the hands of the Amorites so they would destroy us, because He hated us.
05Dt 1:28 Where can we go? Our brothers have discouraged us, saying: The people are larger and taller than we are; the cities are large, fortified to the heavens. We also saw the descendants of the Anakim there.'
05Dt 1:29 "So I said to you: Don't be terrified or afraid of them!
05Dt 1:30 The LORD your God who goes before you will fight for you, just as you saw Him do for you in Egypt.
05Dt 1:31 And you saw in the wilderness how the LORD your God carried you as a man carries his son all along the way you traveled until you reached this place.
05Dt 1:32 But in spite of this you did not trust the LORD your God,
05Dt 1:33 who went before you on the journey to seek out a place for you to camp. He went in the fire by night and in the cloud by day to guide you on the road you were to travel.
05Dt 1:34 "When the LORD heard your words, He grew angry and swore an oath:
05Dt 1:35 'None of these men in this evil generation will see the good land I swore to give your fathers,
05Dt 1:36 except Caleb the son of Jephunneh. He will see it, and I will give him and his descendants the land on which he has set foot, because he followed the LORD completely.'
05Dt 1:37 "The LORD was angry with me also because of you and said: 'You will not enter there either.
05Dt 1:38 Joshua son of Nun, who attends you, will enter it. Encourage him, for he will enable Israel to inherit it.
05Dt 1:39 Your little children who you said would be plunder, your sons who don't know good from evil, will enter there. I will give them the land, and they will take possession of it.
05Dt 1:40 But you are to turn back and head for the wilderness by way of the Red Sea.'
05Dt 1:41 "You answered me, 'We have sinned against the LORD. We will go up and fight just as the LORD our God commanded us.' Then each of you put on his weapons of war and thought it would be easy to go up into the hill country.
05Dt 1:42 "But the LORD said to me, 'Tell them: Don't go up and fight, for I am not with you to keep you from being defeated by your enemies.'
05Dt 1:43 So I spoke to you, but you didn't listen. You rebelled against the LORD's command and defiantly went up into the hill country.
05Dt 1:44 Then the Amorites who lived there came out against you and chased you like a swarm of bees. They routed you from Seir as far as Hormah.
05Dt 1:45 When you returned, you wept before the LORD, but He didn't listen to your requests or pay attention to you.
05Dt 1:46 For this reason you stayed in Kadesh as long as you did.
05Dt 2:1 "Then we turned back and headed for the wilderness by way of the Red Sea, as the LORD had told me, and we traveled around the hill country of Seir for many days.
05Dt 2:2 The LORD then said to me,
05Dt 2:3 'You've been traveling around this hill country long enough; turn north.
05Dt 2:4 Command the people: You are about to travel through the territory of your brothers, the descendants of Esau, who live in Seir. They will be afraid of you, so you must be very careful.
05Dt 2:5 Don't fight with them, for I will not give you any of their land, not even an inch of it, because I have given Esau the hill country of Seir as [his] possession.
05Dt 2:6 You may purchase food from them with silver, so that you may eat, and buy water from them to drink.
05Dt 2:7 For the LORD your God has blessed you in all the work of your hands. He has watched over your journey through this immense wilderness. The LORD your God has been with you this past 40 years, and you have lacked nothing.'
05Dt 2:8 "So we bypassed our brothers, the descendants of Esau, who live in Seir. [We turned] away from the Arabah road and from Elath and Ezion-geber. We traveled along the road to the Wilderness of Moab.
05Dt 2:9 The LORD said to me, 'Show no hostility toward Moab, and do not provoke them to battle, for I will not give you any of their land as a possession, since I have given Ar as a possession to the descendants of Lot.'"
05Dt 2:10 The Emim, a great and numerous people as tall as the Anakim, had previously lived there.
05Dt 2:11 They were also regarded as Rephaim, like the Anakim, though the Moabites called them Emim.
05Dt 2:12 The Horites had previously lived in Seir, but the descendants of Esau drove them out, destroying them completely and settling in their place, just as Israel did in the land of its possession the LORD gave them.
05Dt 2:13 "[The LORD said,] 'Now get up and cross the Zered Valley.' So we crossed the Zered Valley.
05Dt 2:14 The time we spent traveling from Kadesh-barnea until we crossed the Zered Valley was 38 years until the entire generation of fighting men had perished from the camp, as the LORD had sworn to them.
05Dt 2:15 Indeed, the LORD's hand was against them, to eliminate them from the camp until they had all perished.
05Dt 2:16 "When all the fighting men had died among the people,
05Dt 2:17 the LORD spoke to me,
05Dt 2:18 'Today you are going to cross the border of Moab at Ar.
05Dt 2:19 When you get close to the Ammonites, don't show any hostility to them or fight with them, for I will not give you any of the Ammonites' land as a possession; I have given it as a possession to the descendants of Lot.'"
05Dt 2:20 This too used to be regarded as the land of the Rephaim. The Rephaim lived there previously, though the Ammonites called them Zamzummim,
05Dt 2:21 a great and numerous people, tall as the Anakim. The LORD destroyed the Rephaim at the advance of the Ammonites, so that they drove them out and settled in their place.
05Dt 2:22 This was just as He had done for the descendants of Esau who lived in Seir, when He destroyed the Horites before them; they drove them out and have lived in their place until now.
05Dt 2:23 The Caphtorim, who came from Caphtor, destroyed the Avvim, who lived in villages as far as Gaza, and settled in their place.
05Dt 2:24 "[The LORD also said,] 'Get up, move out, and cross the Arnon Valley. See, I have handed Sihon the Amorite, king of Heshbon, and his land over to you. Begin to take possession [of it]; engage him in battle.
05Dt 2:25 Today I will begin to put the fear and dread of you on the peoples everywhere under heaven. They will hear the report about you, tremble, and be in anguish because of you.'
05Dt 2:26 "So I sent messengers with an offer of peace to Sihon king of Heshbon from the Wilderness of Kedemoth, saying,
05Dt 2:27 'Let us travel through your land; we will keep strictly to the highway. We will not turn to the right or the left.
05Dt 2:28 You can sell us food in exchange for silver so we may eat, and give us water for silver so we may drink. Only let us travel through on foot,
05Dt 2:29 just as the descendants of Esau who live in Seir did for us, and the Moabites who live in Ar, until we cross the Jordan into the land the LORD our God is giving us.'
05Dt 2:30 But Sihon king of Heshbon would not let us travel through his land, for the LORD your God made his spirit stubborn and his heart obstinate in order to hand him over to you, as has now taken place.
05Dt 2:31 "Then the LORD said to me, 'See, I have begun to give Sihon and his land to you. Begin to take possession of it.'
05Dt 2:32 So Sihon and his whole army came out against us for battle at Jahaz.
05Dt 2:33 The LORD our God handed him over to us, and we defeated him, his sons, and his whole army.
05Dt 2:34 At that time we captured all his cities and completely destroyed the people of every city, including the women and children. We left no survivors.
05Dt 2:35 We took only the livestock and the spoil from the cities we captured as plunder for ourselves.
05Dt 2:36 There was no city that was inaccessible to us, from Aroer on the rim of the Arnon Valley, along with the city in the valley, even as far as Gilead. The LORD our God gave everything to us.
05Dt 2:37 But you did not go near the Ammonites' land, all along the bank of the Jabbok River and the cities of the hill country, everything that the LORD our God had commanded.
05Dt 3:1 "Then we turned and went up the road to Bashan, and Og king of Bashan, with his whole army, came out against us for battle at Edrei.
05Dt 3:2 But the LORD said to me, 'Do not fear him, for I have handed him over to you, along with his whole army and his land. Do to him as you did to Sihon king of the Amorites, who lived in Heshbon.'
05Dt 3:3 So the LORD our God also handed over Og king of Bashan and his whole army to us. We struck him until there was no survivor left.
05Dt 3:4 We captured all his cities at that time. There wasn't a city that we didn't take from them: 60 cities, the entire region of Argob, the kingdom of Og in Bashan.
05Dt 3:5 All these were fortified with high walls, gates, and bars, besides a large number of rural villages.
05Dt 3:6 We completely destroyed them, as we had done to Sihon king of Heshbon, destroying the men, women, and children of every city.
05Dt 3:7 But we took all the livestock and the spoil from the cities as plunder for ourselves.
05Dt 3:8 "At that time we took the land from the two Amorite kings across the Jordan, from the Arnon Valley as far as Mount Hermon,
05Dt 3:9 which the Sidonians call Sirion, but the Amorites call Senir,
05Dt 3:10 all the cities of the plateau, Gilead, and Bashan as far as Salecah and Edrei, cities of Og's kingdom in Bashan.
05Dt 3:11 (Only Og king of Bashan was left of the remnant of the Rephaim. His bed was made of iron. Isn't it in Rabbah of the Ammonites? It is 13 feet six inches long and six feet wide by a standard measure.)
05Dt 3:12 "At that time we took possession of this land. I gave to the Reubenites and Gadites [the area extending] from Aroer by the Arnon Valley, and half the hill country of Gilead along with its cities.
05Dt 3:13 I gave to half the tribe of Manasseh the rest of Gilead and all Bashan, the kingdom of Og. The entire region of Argob, the whole territory of Bashan, used to be called the land of the Rephaim.
05Dt 3:14 Jair, a descendant of Manasseh, took over the entire region of Argob as far as the border of the Geshurites and Maacathites. He called Bashan by his own name, Jair's Villages, as it is today.
05Dt 3:15 I gave Gilead to Machir,
05Dt 3:16 and I gave to the Reubenites and Gadites [the area extending] from Gilead to the Arnon Valley (the middle of the valley was the border) and up to the Jabbok River, the border of the Ammonites.
05Dt 3:17 The Arabah and Jordan are also borders from Chinnereth as far as the Sea of the Arabah, the Dead Sea, under the slopes of Pisgah on the east.
05Dt 3:18 "I commanded you at that time: The LORD your God has given you this land to possess. All your fighting men will cross over in battle formation ahead of your brothers the Israelites.
05Dt 3:19 But your wives, young children, and livestock-- I know that you have a lot of livestock-- will remain in the cities I have given you
05Dt 3:20 until the LORD gives rest to your brothers as He has to you, and they also take possession of the land the LORD your God is giving them across the Jordan. Then each of you may return to his possession that I have given you.
05Dt 3:21 "I commanded Joshua at that time: Your own eyes have seen everything the LORD your God has done to these two kings. The LORD will do the same to all the kingdoms you are about to enter.
05Dt 3:22 Don't be afraid of them, for the LORD your God fights for you.
05Dt 3:23 "At that time I begged the LORD:
05Dt 3:24 Lord God, You have begun to show Your greatness and power to Your servant, for what god is there in heaven or on earth who can perform deeds and mighty acts like Yours?
05Dt 3:25 Please let me cross over and see the beautiful land on the other side of the Jordan, that good hill country and Lebanon.
05Dt 3:26 "But the LORD was angry with me on account of you and would not listen to me. The LORD said to me, 'That's enough! Do not speak to Me again about this matter.
05Dt 3:27 Go to the top of Pisgah and look to the west, north, south, and east, and see [it] with your own eyes, for you will not cross this Jordan.
05Dt 3:28 But commission Joshua and encourage and strengthen him, for he will cross over ahead of the people and enable them to inherit this land that you will see.'
05Dt 3:29 So we stayed in the valley facing Beth-peor.
05Dt 4:1 "Now, Israel, listen to the statutes and ordinances I am teaching you to follow, so that you may live, enter, and take possession of the land the LORD, the God of your fathers, is giving you.
05Dt 4:2 You must not add anything to what I command you or take anything away from it, so that you may keep the commands of the LORD your God I am giving you.
05Dt 4:3 Your eyes have seen what the LORD did at Baal-peor, for the LORD your God destroyed every one of you who followed Baal of Peor.
05Dt 4:4 But you who have remained faithful to the LORD your God are all alive today.
05Dt 4:5 Look, I have taught you statutes and ordinances as the LORD my God has commanded me, so that you may follow them in the land you are entering to possess.
05Dt 4:6 Carefully follow [them], for this will [show] your wisdom and understanding in the eyes of the peoples. When they hear about all these statutes, they will say, 'This great nation is indeed a wise and understanding people.'
05Dt 4:7 For what great nation is there that has a god near to it as the LORD our God is [to us] whenever we call to Him?
05Dt 4:8 And what great nation has righteous statutes and ordinances like this entire law I set before you today?
05Dt 4:9 "Only be on your guard and diligently watch yourselves, so that you don't forget the things your eyes have seen and so that they don't slip from your mind as long as you live. Teach them to your children and your grandchildren.
05Dt 4:10 The day you stood before the LORD your God at Horeb, the LORD said to me, 'Assemble the people before Me, and I will let them hear My words, so that they may learn to fear Me all the days they live on the earth and may instruct their children.'
05Dt 4:11 You came near and stood at the base of the mountain, a mountain blazing with fire into the heavens and enveloped in a dense, black cloud.
05Dt 4:12 Then the LORD spoke to you from the fire. You kept hearing the sound of the words, but didn't see a form; there was only a voice.
05Dt 4:13 He declared His covenant to you. He commanded you to follow the Ten Commandments, which He wrote on two stone tablets.
05Dt 4:14 At that time the LORD commanded me to teach you statutes and ordinances for you to follow in the land you are about to cross into and possess.
05Dt 4:15 "Be extremely careful for your own good-- because you did not see any form on the day the LORD spoke to you at Horeb out of the fire--
05Dt 4:16 not to act corruptly and make an idol for yourselves in the shape of any figure: a male or female form,
05Dt 4:17 or the form of any beast on the earth, any winged creature that flies in the sky,
05Dt 4:18 any creature that crawls on the ground, or any fish in the waters under the earth.
05Dt 4:19 When you look to the heavens and see the sun, moon, and stars-- all the array of heaven-- do not be led astray to bow down and worship them. The LORD your God has provided them for all people everywhere under heaven.
05Dt 4:20 But the LORD selected you and brought you out of Egypt's iron furnace to be a people for His inheritance, as you are today.
05Dt 4:21 "The LORD was angry with me on your account. He swore that I would not cross the Jordan and enter the good land the LORD your God is giving you as an inheritance.
05Dt 4:22 I won't be crossing the Jordan because I am going to die in this land. But you are about to cross over and take possession of this good land.
05Dt 4:23 Be careful not to forget the covenant of the LORD your God that He made with you, and make an idol for yourselves in the shape of anything He has forbidden you.
05Dt 4:24 For the LORD your God is a consuming fire, a jealous God.
05Dt 4:25 "When you have children and grandchildren and have been in the land a long time, and if you act corruptly, make an idol in the form of anything, and do what is evil in the sight of the LORD your God, provoking Him to anger,
05Dt 4:26 I call heaven and earth as witnesses against you today that you will quickly perish from the land you are about to cross the Jordan to possess. You will not live long there, but you will certainly be destroyed.
05Dt 4:27 The LORD will scatter you among the peoples, and you will be reduced to a few survivors among the nations where the LORD your God will drive you.
05Dt 4:28 There you will worship man-made gods of wood and stone, which cannot see, hear, eat, or smell.
05Dt 4:29 But from there, you will search for the LORD your God, and you will find [Him] when you seek Him with all your heart and all your soul.
05Dt 4:30 When you are in distress and all these things have happened to you, you will return to the LORD your God in later days and obey Him.
05Dt 4:31 He will not leave you, destroy you, or forget the covenant with your fathers that He swore to them by oath, because the LORD your God is a compassionate God.
05Dt 4:32 "Indeed, ask about the earlier days that preceded you, from the day God created man on the earth and from one end of the heavens to the other: Has anything like this great event [ever] happened, or has anything like it been heard of?
05Dt 4:33 Has a people ever heard God's voice speaking from the fire as you have, and lived?
05Dt 4:34 Or has a god [ever] attempted to go and take a nation as his own out of [another] nation, by trials, signs, wonders, and war, by a strong hand and an outstretched arm, by great terrors, as the LORD your God did for you in Egypt before your eyes?
05Dt 4:35 You were shown [these things] so that you would know that the LORD is God; there is no other besides Him.
05Dt 4:36 He let you hear His voice from heaven to instruct you. He showed you His great fire on earth, and you heard His words from the fire.
05Dt 4:37 Because He loved your fathers, He chose their descendants after them and brought you out of Egypt by His presence and great power,
05Dt 4:38 to drive out before you nations greater and stronger than you and to bring you in and give you their land as an inheritance, as is now taking place.
05Dt 4:39 Today, recognize and keep in mind that the LORD is God in heaven above and on earth below; there is no other.
05Dt 4:40 Keep His statutes and commands, which I am giving you today, so that you and your children after you may prosper and so that you may live long in the land the LORD your God is giving you for all time."
05Dt 4:41 Then Moses set apart three cities across the Jordan to the east,
05Dt 4:42 where one could flee who committed manslaughter and killed his neighbor accidentally without previously hating him. He could flee to one of these cities and stay alive:
05Dt 4:43 Bezer in the wilderness on the plateau land, belonging to the Reubenites; Ramoth in Gilead, belonging to the Gadites; or Golan in Bashan, belonging to the Manassites.
05Dt 4:44 This is the law Moses gave the Israelites.
05Dt 4:45 These are the decrees, statutes, and ordinances Moses proclaimed to them after they came out of Egypt,
05Dt 4:46 across the Jordan in the valley facing Beth-peor in the land of Sihon king of the Amorites. He lived in Heshbon, and Moses and the Israelites defeated him after they came out of Egypt.
05Dt 4:47 They took possession of his land and the land of Og king of Bashan, the two Amorite kings who were across the Jordan to the east,
05Dt 4:48 from Aroer on the rim of the Arnon Valley as far as Mount Sion (that is, Hermon)
05Dt 4:49 and all the Arabah on the east side of the Jordan as far as the Dead Sea below the slopes of Pisgah.
05Dt 5:1 Moses summoned all Israel and said to them, "Israel, listen to the statutes and ordinances I am proclaiming as you hear them today. Learn and follow them carefully.
05Dt 5:2 The LORD our God made a covenant with us at Horeb.
05Dt 5:3 He did not make this covenant with our fathers, but with all of us who are alive here today.
05Dt 5:4 The LORD spoke to you face to face from the fire on the mountain.
05Dt 5:5 At that time I was standing between the LORD and you to report the word of the LORD to you, because you were afraid of the fire and did not go up the mountain. And He said:
05Dt 5:6 I am the LORD your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the place of slavery.
05Dt 5:7 Do not have other gods besides Me.
05Dt 5:8 Do not make an idol for yourself in the shape of anything in the heavens above or on the earth below or in the waters under the earth.
05Dt 5:9 You must not bow down to them or worship them, because I, the LORD your God, am a jealous God, punishing the children for the fathers' sin to the third and fourth [generations] of those who hate Me,
05Dt 5:10 but showing faithful love to a thousand [generations] of those who love Me and keep My commands.
05Dt 5:11 Do not misuse the name of the LORD your God, because the LORD will punish anyone who misuses His name.
05Dt 5:12 Be careful to dedicate the Sabbath day, as the LORD your God has commanded you.
05Dt 5:13 You are to labor six days and do all your work,
05Dt 5:14 but the seventh day is a Sabbath to the LORD your God. You must not do any work-- you, your son or daughter, your male or female slave, your ox or donkey, any of your livestock, or the foreigner who lives within your gates, so that your male and female slaves may rest as you do.
05Dt 5:15 Remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt, and the LORD your God brought you out of there with a strong hand and an outstretched arm. That is why the LORD your God has commanded you to keep the Sabbath day.
05Dt 5:16 Honor your father and your mother, as the LORD your God has commanded you, so that you may live long and so that you may prosper in the land the LORD your God is giving you.
05Dt 5:17 Do not murder.
05Dt 5:18 Do not commit adultery.
05Dt 5:19 Do not steal.
05Dt 5:20 Do not give dishonest testimony against your neighbor.
05Dt 5:21 Do not desire your neighbor's wife or covet your neighbor's house, his field, his male or female slave, his ox or donkey, or anything that belongs to your neighbor.
05Dt 5:22 "The LORD spoke these commands in a loud voice to your entire assembly from the fire, cloud, and thick darkness on the mountain; He added nothing more. He wrote them on two stone tablets and gave them to me.
05Dt 5:23 All of you approached me with your tribal leaders and elders when you heard the voice from the darkness and while the mountain was blazing with fire.
05Dt 5:24 You said, 'Look, the LORD our God has shown us His glory and greatness, and we have heard His voice from the fire. Today we have seen that God speaks with a person, yet he still lives.
05Dt 5:25 But now, why should we die? This great fire will consume us and we will die if we hear the voice of the LORD our God any longer.
05Dt 5:26 For who out of all mankind has heard the voice of the living God speaking from the fire, as we have, and lived?
05Dt 5:27 Go near and listen to everything the LORD our God says. Then you can tell us everything the LORD our God tells you; we will listen and obey.'
05Dt 5:28 "The LORD heard your words when you spoke to me. He said to me, 'I have heard the words that these people have spoken to you. Everything they have said is right.
05Dt 5:29 If only they had such a heart to fear Me and keep all My commands, so that they and their children will prosper forever.
05Dt 5:30 Go and tell them: Return to your tents.
05Dt 5:31 But you stand here with Me, and I will tell you every command-- the statutes and ordinances-- you are to teach them, so that they may follow [them] in the land I am giving them to possess.'
05Dt 5:32 "Be careful to do as the LORD your God has commanded you; you are not to turn aside to the right or the left.
05Dt 5:33 Follow the whole instruction the LORD your God has commanded you, so that you may live, prosper, and have a long life in the land you will possess.
05Dt 6:1 "This is the command-- the statutes and ordinances-- the LORD your God has instructed [me] to teach you, so that you may follow [them] in the land you are about to enter and possess.
05Dt 6:2 [Do this] so that you may fear the LORD your God all the days of your life by keeping all His statutes and commands I am giving you, your son, and your grandson, and so that you may have a long life.
05Dt 6:3 Listen, Israel, and be careful to follow [them], so that you may prosper and multiply greatly, because the LORD, the God of your fathers, has promised you a land flowing with milk and honey.
05Dt 6:4 "Listen, Israel: The LORD our God, the LORD is One.
05Dt 6:5 Love the LORD your God with all your heart, with all your soul, and with all your strength.
05Dt 6:6 These words that I am giving you today are to be in your heart.
05Dt 6:7 Repeat them to your children. Talk about them when you sit in your house and when you walk along the road, when you lie down and when you get up.
05Dt 6:8 Bind them as a sign on your hand and let them be a symbol on your forehead.
05Dt 6:9 Write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates.
05Dt 6:10 "When the LORD your God brings you into the land He swore to your fathers Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob that He would give you-- a [land with] large and beautiful cities that you did not build,
05Dt 6:11 houses full of every good thing that you did not fill [them with], wells dug that you did not dig, and vineyards and olive groves that you did not plant-- and when you eat and are satisfied,
05Dt 6:12 be careful not to forget the LORD who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the place of slavery.
05Dt 6:13 Fear the LORD your God, worship Him, and take [your] oaths in His name.
05Dt 6:14 Do not follow other gods, the gods of the peoples around you,
05Dt 6:15 for the LORD your God, who is among you, is a jealous God. Otherwise, the LORD your God will become angry with you and wipe you off the face of the earth.
05Dt 6:16 Do not test the LORD your God as you tested [Him] at Massah.
05Dt 6:17 Carefully observe the commands of the LORD your God, the decrees and statutes He has commanded you.
05Dt 6:18 Do what is right and good in the LORD's sight, so that you may prosper and so that you may enter and possess the good land the LORD your God swore to [give] your fathers,
05Dt 6:19 by driving out all your enemies before you, as the LORD has said.
05Dt 6:20 "When your son asks you in the future, 'What is the meaning of the decrees, statutes, and ordinances, which the LORD our God has commanded you?'
05Dt 6:21 tell him, 'We were slaves of Pharaoh in Egypt, but the LORD brought us out of Egypt with a strong hand.
05Dt 6:22 Before our eyes the LORD inflicted great and devastating signs and wonders on Egypt, on Pharaoh and all his household,
05Dt 6:23 but He brought us from there in order to lead us in and give us the land that He swore to our fathers.
05Dt 6:24 The LORD commanded us to follow all these statutes and to fear the LORD our God for our prosperity always and for our preservation, as it is today.
05Dt 6:25 Righteousness will be ours if we are careful to follow every one of these commands before the LORD our God, as He has commanded us.'
05Dt 7:1 "When the LORD your God brings you into the land you are entering to possess, and He drives out many nations before you-- the Hittites, Girgashites, Amorites, Canaanites, Perizzites, Hivites and Jebusites, seven nations more numerous and powerful than you--
05Dt 7:2 and when the LORD your God delivers them over to you and you defeat them, you must completely destroy them. Make no treaty with them and show them no mercy.
05Dt 7:3 Do not intermarry with them. Do not give your daughters to their sons or take their daughters for your sons,
05Dt 7:4 because they will turn your sons away from Me to worship other gods. Then the LORD's anger will burn against you, and He will swiftly destroy you.
05Dt 7:5 Instead, this is what you are to do to them: tear down their altars, smash their standing pillars, cut down their Asherah poles, and burn up their carved images.
05Dt 7:6 For you are a holy people belonging to the LORD your God. The LORD your God has chosen you to be His own possession out of all the peoples on the face of the earth.
05Dt 7:7 "The LORD was devoted to you and chose you, not because you were more numerous than all peoples, for you were the fewest of all peoples.
05Dt 7:8 But because the LORD loved you and kept the oath He swore to your fathers, He brought you out with a strong hand and redeemed you from the place of slavery, from the power of Pharaoh king of Egypt.
05Dt 7:9 Know that Yahweh your God is God, the faithful God who keeps His gracious covenant loyalty for a thousand generations with those who love Him and keep His commands.
05Dt 7:10 But He directly pays back and destroys those who hate Him. He will not hesitate to directly pay back the one who hates Him.
05Dt 7:11 So keep the command-- the statutes and ordinances-- that I am giving you to follow today.
05Dt 7:12 "If you listen to and are careful to keep these ordinances, the LORD your God will keep His covenant loyalty with you, as He swore to your fathers.
05Dt 7:13 He will love you, bless you, and multiply you. He will bless your descendants, and the produce of your soil-- your grain, new wine, and oil-- the young of your herds, and the newborn of your flocks, in the land He swore to your fathers that He would give you.
05Dt 7:14 You will be blessed above all peoples; there will be no infertile male or female among you or your livestock.
05Dt 7:15 The LORD will remove all sickness from you; He will not put on you all the terrible diseases of Egypt that you know about, but He will inflict them on all who hate you.
05Dt 7:16 You must destroy all the peoples the LORD your God is delivering over to you and not look on them with pity. Do not worship their gods, for that will be a snare to you.
05Dt 7:17 "If you say to yourself, 'These nations are greater than I; how can I drive them out?'
05Dt 7:18 do not be afraid of them. Be sure to remember what the LORD your God did to Pharaoh and all Egypt:
05Dt 7:19 the great trials that you saw, the signs and wonders, the strong hand and outstretched arm, by which the LORD your God brought you out. The LORD your God will do the same to all the peoples you fear.
05Dt 7:20 The LORD your God will also send the hornet against them until all the survivors and those hiding from you perish.
05Dt 7:21 Don't be terrified of them, for the LORD your God, a great and awesome God, is among you.
05Dt 7:22 The LORD your God will drive out these nations before you little by little. You will not be able to destroy them all at once; otherwise, the wild animals will become too numerous for you.
05Dt 7:23 The LORD your God will give them over to you and throw them into great confusion until they are destroyed.
05Dt 7:24 He will hand their kings over to you, and you will wipe out their names under heaven. No one will be able to stand against you; you will annihilate them.
05Dt 7:25 You must burn up the carved images of their gods. Don't covet the silver and gold on the images and take it for yourself, or else you will be ensnared by it, for it is abhorrent to the LORD your God.
05Dt 7:26 You must not bring any abhorrent thing into your house, or you will be set apart for destruction like it. You are to utterly detest and abhor it, because it is set apart for destruction.
05Dt 8:1 "You must carefully follow every command I am giving you today, so that you may live and increase, and may enter and take possession of the land the LORD swore to your fathers.
05Dt 8:2 Remember that the LORD your God led you on the entire journey these 40 years in the wilderness, so that He might humble you and test you to know what was in your heart, whether or not you would keep His commands.
05Dt 8:3 He humbled you by letting you go hungry; then He gave you manna to eat, which you and your fathers had not known, so that you might learn that man does not live on bread alone but on every word that comes from the mouth of the LORD.
05Dt 8:4 Your clothing did not wear out, and your feet did not swell these 40 years.
05Dt 8:5 Keep in mind that the LORD your God has been disciplining you just as a man disciplines his son.
05Dt 8:6 So keep the commands of the LORD your God by walking in His ways and fearing Him.
05Dt 8:7 For the LORD your God is bringing you into a good land, a land with streams of water, springs, and deep water sources, flowing in both valleys and hills;
05Dt 8:8 a land of wheat, barley, vines, figs, and pomegranates; a land of olive oil and honey;
05Dt 8:9 a land where you will eat food without shortage, where you will lack nothing; a land whose rocks are iron and from whose hills you will mine copper.
05Dt 8:10 When you eat and are full, you will praise the LORD your God for the good land He has given you.
05Dt 8:11 "Be careful that you don't forget the LORD your God by failing to keep His command-- the ordinances and statutes-- I am giving you today.
05Dt 8:12 When you eat and are full, and build beautiful houses to live in,
05Dt 8:13 and your herds and flocks grow large, and your silver and gold multiply, and everything else you have increases,
05Dt 8:14 [be careful] that your heart doesn't become proud and you forget the LORD your God who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the place of slavery.
05Dt 8:15 He led you through the great and terrible wilderness with its poisonous snakes and scorpions, a thirsty land where there was no water. He brought water out of the flintlike rock for you.
05Dt 8:16 He fed you in the wilderness with manna that your fathers had not known, in order to humble and test you, so that in the end He might cause you to prosper.
05Dt 8:17 You may say to yourself, 'My power and my own ability have gained this wealth for me,'
05Dt 8:18 but remember that the LORD your God gives you the power to gain wealth, in order to confirm His covenant He swore to your fathers, as it is today.
05Dt 8:19 If you ever forget the LORD your God and go after other gods to worship and bow down to them, I testify against you today that you will perish.
05Dt 8:20 Like the nations the LORD is about to destroy before you, you will perish if you do not obey the LORD your God.
05Dt 9:1 "Listen, Israel: Today you are about to cross the Jordan to go and drive out nations greater and stronger than you [with] large cities fortified to the heavens.
05Dt 9:2 The people are strong and tall, the descendants of the Anakim. You know about them and you have heard it said about them, 'Who can stand up to the sons of Anak?'
05Dt 9:3 But understand that today the LORD your God will cross over ahead of you as a consuming fire; He will devastate and subdue them before you. You will drive them out and destroy them swiftly, as the LORD has told you.
05Dt 9:4 When the LORD your God drives them out before you, do not say to yourself, 'The LORD brought me in to take possession of this land because of my righteousness.' Instead, the LORD will drive out these nations before you because of their wickedness.
05Dt 9:5 You are not going to take possession of their land because of your righteousness or your integrity. Instead, the LORD your God will drive out these nations before you because of their wickedness, in order to keep the promise He swore to your fathers, Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.
05Dt 9:6 Understand that the LORD your God is not giving you this good land to possess because of your righteousness, for you are a stiff-necked people.
05Dt 9:7 "Remember and do not forget how you provoked the LORD your God in the wilderness. You have been rebelling against the LORD from the day you left the land of Egypt until you reached this place.
05Dt 9:8 You provoked the LORD at Horeb, and He was angry enough with you to destroy you.
05Dt 9:9 When I went up the mountain to receive the stone tablets, the tablets of the covenant the LORD made with you, I stayed on the mountain 40 days and 40 nights. I did not eat bread or drink water.
05Dt 9:10 On the day of the assembly the LORD gave me the two stone tablets, inscribed by God's finger. The exact words were on them, which the LORD spoke to you from the fire on the mountain.
05Dt 9:11 The LORD gave me the two stone tablets, the tablets of the covenant, at the end of the 40 days and 40 nights.
05Dt 9:12 "The LORD said to me, 'Get up and go down immediately from here. For your people you brought out of Egypt have acted corruptly. They have quickly turned from the way that I commanded them; they have made a cast image for themselves.'
05Dt 9:13 The LORD also said to me, 'I have seen this people, and indeed, they are a stiff-necked people.
05Dt 9:14 Leave Me alone, and I will destroy them and blot out their name under heaven. Then I will make you into a nation stronger and more numerous than they.'
05Dt 9:15 "So I went back down the mountain, while it was blazing with fire, and the two tablets of the covenant were in my hands.
05Dt 9:16 I saw how you had sinned against the LORD your God; you had made a calf image for yourselves. You had quickly turned from the way the LORD had commanded for you.
05Dt 9:17 So I took hold of the tablets and threw them from my hands, shattering them before your eyes.
05Dt 9:18 Then I fell down like the first time in the presence of the LORD for 40 days and 40 nights; I did not eat bread or drink water because of all the sin you committed, doing what was evil in the LORD's sight and provoking Him to anger.
05Dt 9:19 I was afraid of the fierce anger the LORD had directed against you, because He was about to destroy you. But again, the LORD listened to me on that occasion.
05Dt 9:20 The LORD was angry enough with Aaron to destroy him. But I prayed for Aaron at that time also.
05Dt 9:21 I took the sinful calf you had made, burned it up, and crushed it, thoroughly grinding it to powder as [fine as] dust. Then I threw it into the stream that came down from the mountain.
05Dt 9:22 "You continued to provoke the LORD at Taberah, Massah, and Kibroth-hattaavah.
05Dt 9:23 When the LORD sent you from Kadesh-barnea, He said, 'Go up and possess the land I have given you'; you rebelled against the command of the LORD your God. You did not believe or obey Him.
05Dt 9:24 You have been rebelling against the LORD ever since I have known you.
05Dt 9:25 "I fell down in the presence of the LORD 40 days and 40 nights because the LORD had threatened to destroy you.
05Dt 9:26 I prayed to the LORD: Lord God, do not annihilate Your people, Your inheritance, whom You redeemed through Your greatness and brought out of Egypt with a strong hand.
05Dt 9:27 Remember Your servants Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. Disregard this people's stubbornness, and their wickedness and sin.
05Dt 9:28 Otherwise, those in the land you brought us from will say, 'Because the LORD wasn't able to bring them into the land He had promised them, and because He hated them, He brought them out to kill them in the wilderness.'
05Dt 9:29 But they are Your people, Your inheritance, whom You brought out by Your great power and outstretched arm.
05Dt 10:1 "The LORD said to me at that time, 'Cut two stone tablets like the first ones and come to Me on the mountain and make a wooden ark.
05Dt 10:2 I will write on the tablets the words that were on the first tablets you broke, and you are to place them in the ark.'
05Dt 10:3 So I made an ark of acacia wood, cut two stone tablets like the first ones, and climbed the mountain with the two tablets in my hand.
05Dt 10:4 Then, on the day of the assembly, the LORD wrote on the tablets what had been written previously, the Ten Commandments that He had spoken to you on the mountain from the fire. The LORD gave them to me,
05Dt 10:5 and I went back down the mountain and placed the tablets in the ark I had made. And they have remained there, as the LORD commanded me."
05Dt 10:6 The Israelites traveled from Beeroth Bene-jaakan to Moserah. Aaron died and was buried there, and Eleazar his son became priest in his place.
05Dt 10:7 They traveled from there to Gudgodah, and from Gudgodah to Jotbathah, a land with streams of water.
05Dt 10:8 "At that time the LORD set apart the tribe of Levi to carry the ark of the LORD's covenant, to stand before the LORD to serve Him, and to bless in His name, as it is today.
05Dt 10:9 For this reason, Levi does not have a portion or inheritance like his brothers; the LORD is his inheritance, as the LORD your God told him.
05Dt 10:10 "I stayed on the mountain 40 days and 40 nights like the first time. The LORD also listened to me on this occasion; He agreed not to annihilate you.
05Dt 10:11 Then the LORD said to me, 'Get up. Continue your journey ahead of the people, so that they may enter and possess the land I swore to give their fathers.'
05Dt 10:12 "And now, Israel, what does the LORD your God ask of you except to fear the LORD your God by walking in all His ways, to love Him, and to worship the LORD your God with all your heart and all your soul?
05Dt 10:13 Keep the LORD's commands and statutes I am giving you today, for your own good.
05Dt 10:14 The heavens, indeed the highest heavens, belong to the LORD your God, as does the earth and everything in it.
05Dt 10:15 Yet the LORD was devoted to your fathers and loved them. He chose their descendants after them-- [He chose] you out of all the peoples, as it is today.
05Dt 10:16 Therefore, circumcise your hearts and don't be stiff-necked any longer.
05Dt 10:17 For the LORD your God is the God of gods and Lord of lords, the great, mighty, and awesome God, showing no partiality and taking no bribe.
05Dt 10:18 He executes justice for the fatherless and the widow, and loves the foreign resident, giving him food and clothing.
05Dt 10:19 You also must love the foreigner, since you were foreigners in the land of Egypt.
05Dt 10:20 You are to fear the LORD your God and worship Him. Remain faithful to Him and take oaths in His name.
05Dt 10:21 He is your praise and He is your God, who has done for you these great and awesome works your eyes have seen.
05Dt 10:22 Your fathers went down to Egypt, 70 people in all, and now the LORD your God has made you as numerous as the stars of the sky.
05Dt 11:1 "Therefore, love the LORD your God and always keep His mandate and His statutes, ordinances, and commands.
05Dt 11:2 You must understand today that it is not your children who experienced or saw the discipline of the LORD your God: His greatness, strong hand, and outstretched arm;
05Dt 11:3 His signs and the works He did in Egypt to Pharaoh king of Egypt and all his land;
05Dt 11:4 what He did to Egypt's army, its horses and chariots, when He made the waters of the Red Sea flow over them as they pursued you, and He destroyed them completely;
05Dt 11:5 what He did to you in the wilderness until you reached this place;
05Dt 11:6 and what He did to Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab the Reubenite, when in the middle of the whole Israelite [camp] the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them, their households, their tents, and every living thing with them.
05Dt 11:7 Your [own] eyes have seen every great work the LORD has done.
05Dt 11:8 "Keep every command I am giving you today, so that you may have the strength to cross into and possess the land you are to inherit,
05Dt 11:9 and so that you may live long in the land the LORD swore to your fathers to give them and their descendants, a land flowing with milk and honey.
05Dt 11:10 For the land you are entering to possess is not like the land of Egypt, from which you have come, where you sowed your seed and irrigated by hand as in a vegetable garden.
05Dt 11:11 But the land you are entering to possess is a land of mountains and valleys, watered by rain from the sky.
05Dt 11:12 It is a land the LORD your God cares for. He is always watching over it from the beginning to the end of the year.
05Dt 11:13 "If you carefully obey My commands I am giving you today, to love the LORD your God and worship Him with all your heart and all your soul,
05Dt 11:14 I will provide rain for your land in season, the early and late rains, and you will harvest your grain, new wine, and oil.
05Dt 11:15 I will provide grass in your fields for your livestock. You will eat and be satisfied.
05Dt 11:16 Be careful that you are not enticed to turn aside, worship, and bow down to other gods.
05Dt 11:17 Then the LORD's anger will burn against you. He will close the sky, and there will be no rain; the land will not yield its produce, and you will perish quickly from the good land the LORD is giving you.
05Dt 11:18 "Impress these words of Mine on your hearts and souls, bind them as a sign on your hands, and let them be a symbol on your foreheads.
05Dt 11:19 Teach them to your children, talking about them when you sit in your house and when you walk along the road, when you lie down and when you get up.
05Dt 11:20 Write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates,
05Dt 11:21 so that as long as the heavens are above the earth, your days and those of your children may be many in the land the LORD swore to give your fathers.
05Dt 11:22 For if you carefully observe every one of these commands I am giving you to follow-- to love the LORD your God, walk in all His ways, and remain faithful to Him--
05Dt 11:23 the LORD will drive out all these nations before you, and you will drive out nations greater and stronger than you are.
05Dt 11:24 Every place the sole of your foot treads will be yours. Your territory will extend from the wilderness to Lebanon and from the Euphrates River to the Mediterranean Sea.
05Dt 11:25 No one will be able to stand against you; the LORD your God will put fear and dread of you in all the land where you set foot, as He has promised you.
05Dt 11:26 "Look, today I set before you a blessing and a curse:
05Dt 11:27 [there will be] a blessing, if you obey the commands of the LORD your God I am giving you today,
05Dt 11:28 and a curse, if you do not obey the commands of the LORD your God, and you turn aside from the path I command you today by following other gods you have not known.
05Dt 11:29 When the LORD your God brings you into the land you are entering to possess, you are to proclaim the blessing at Mount Gerizim and the curse at Mount Ebal.
05Dt 11:30 Aren't these mountains across the Jordan, beyond the western road in the land of the Canaanites, who live in the Arabah, opposite Gilgal, near the oaks of Moreh?
05Dt 11:31 For you are about to cross the Jordan to enter and take possession of the land the LORD your God is giving you. When you possess it and settle in it,
05Dt 11:32 be careful to follow all the statutes and ordinances I set before you today.
05Dt 12:1 "Be careful to follow these statutes and ordinances in the land that the LORD, the God of your fathers, has given you to possess all the days you live on the earth.
05Dt 12:2 Destroy completely all the places where the nations you are driving out worship their gods-- on the high mountains, on the hills, and under every flourishing tree.
05Dt 12:3 Tear down their altars, smash their sacred pillars, burn up their Asherah poles, cut down the carved images of their gods, and wipe out their names from every place.
05Dt 12:4 Don't worship the LORD your God this way.
05Dt 12:5 Instead, you must go to the place the LORD your God chooses from all your tribes to put His name for His dwelling.
05Dt 12:6 You are to bring there your burnt offerings and sacrifices, your tenths and personal contributions, your vow offerings and freewill offerings, and the firstborn of your herds and flocks.
05Dt 12:7 You will eat there in the presence of the LORD your God and rejoice with your household in everything you do, because the LORD your God has blessed you.
05Dt 12:8 "You are not to do as we are doing here today; everyone [is doing] whatever seems right in his own eyes.
05Dt 12:9 Indeed, you have not yet come into the resting place and the inheritance the LORD your God is giving you.
05Dt 12:10 When you cross the Jordan and live in the land the LORD your God is giving you to inherit, and He gives you rest from all the enemies around you and you live in security,
05Dt 12:11 then the LORD your God will choose the place to have His name dwell. Bring there everything I command you: your burnt offerings, sacrifices, offerings of the tenth, personal contributions, and all your choice offerings you vow to the LORD.
05Dt 12:12 You will rejoice before the LORD your God-- you, your sons and daughters, your male and female slaves, and the Levite who is within your gates, since he has no portion or inheritance among you.
05Dt 12:13 Be careful not to offer your burnt offerings in all the [sacred] places you see.
05Dt 12:14 You must offer your burnt offerings only in the place the LORD chooses in one of your tribes, and there you must do everything I command you.
05Dt 12:15 "But whenever you want, you may slaughter and eat meat within any of your gates, according to the blessing the LORD your God has given you. Those who are clean or unclean may eat it, as they would a gazelle or deer,
05Dt 12:16 but you must not eat the blood; pour it on the ground like water.
05Dt 12:17 Within your gates you may not eat: the tenth of your grain, new wine, or oil; the firstborn of your herd or flock; any of your vow offerings that you pledge; your freewill offerings; or your personal contributions.
05Dt 12:18 You must eat them in the presence of the LORD your God at the place the LORD your God chooses-- you, your son and daughter, your male and female slave, and the Levite who is within your gates. Rejoice before the LORD your God in everything you do,
05Dt 12:19 and be careful not to neglect the Levite, as long as you live in your land.
05Dt 12:20 "When the LORD your God enlarges your territory as He has promised you, and you say, 'I want to eat meat' because you have a strong desire to eat meat, you may eat it whenever you want.
05Dt 12:21 If the place where the LORD your God chooses to put His name is too far from you, you may slaughter any of your herd or flock He has given you, as I have commanded you, and you may eat it within your gates whenever you want.
05Dt 12:22 Indeed, you may eat it as the gazelle and deer are eaten; both the clean and the unclean may eat it.
05Dt 12:23 But don't eat the blood, since the blood is the life, and you must not eat the life with the meat.
05Dt 12:24 Do not eat blood; pour it on the ground like water.
05Dt 12:25 Do not eat it, so that you and your children after you will prosper, because you will be doing what is right in the LORD's sight.
05Dt 12:26 "But you are to take the holy offerings you have and your vow offerings and go to the place the LORD chooses.
05Dt 12:27 Present the meat and blood of your burnt offerings on the altar of the LORD your God. The blood of your [other] sacrifices is to be poured out beside the altar of the LORD your God, but you may eat the meat.
05Dt 12:28 Be careful to obey all these things I command you, so that you and your children after you may prosper forever, because you will be doing what is good and right in the sight of the LORD your God.
05Dt 12:29 "When the LORD your God annihilates the nations before you, which you are entering to take possession of, and you drive them out and live in their land,
05Dt 12:30 be careful not to be ensnared by their ways after they have been destroyed before you. Do not inquire about their gods, asking, 'How did these nations worship their gods? I'll also do the same.'
05Dt 12:31 You must not do the same to the LORD your God, because they practice for their gods every detestable thing the LORD hates. They even burn their sons and daughters in the fire to their gods.
05Dt 12:32  You must be careful to do everything I command you; do not add anything to it or take anything away from it.
05Dt 13:1 "If a prophet or someone who has dreams arises among you and proclaims a sign or wonder to you,
05Dt 13:2 and that sign or wonder he has promised you comes about, but he says, 'Let us follow other gods,' which you have not known, 'and let us worship them,'
05Dt 13:3 do not listen to that prophet's words or to that dreamer. For the LORD your God is testing you to know whether you love the LORD your God with all your heart and all your soul.
05Dt 13:4 You must follow the LORD your God and fear Him. You must keep His commands and listen to His voice; you must worship Him and remain faithful to Him.
05Dt 13:5 That prophet or dreamer must be put to death, because he has urged rebellion against the LORD your God who brought you out of the land of Egypt and redeemed you from the place of slavery, to turn you from the way the LORD your God has commanded you to walk. You must purge the evil from you.
05Dt 13:6 "If your brother, the son of your mother, or your son or daughter, or the wife you embrace, or your closest friend secretly entices you, saying, 'Let us go and worship other gods'-- which neither you nor your fathers have known,
05Dt 13:7 any of the gods of the peoples around you, near you or far from you, from one end of the earth to the other--
05Dt 13:8 you must not yield to him or listen to him. Show him no pity, and do not spare [him] or shield him.
05Dt 13:9 Instead, you must kill him. Your hand is to be the first against him to put him to death, and then the hands of all the people.
05Dt 13:10 Stone him to death for trying to turn you away from the LORD your God who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the place of slavery.
05Dt 13:11 All Israel will hear and be afraid, and they will no longer do anything evil like this among you.
05Dt 13:12 "If you hear it said about one of your cities the LORD your God is giving you to live in,
05Dt 13:13 that wicked men have sprung up among you, led the inhabitants of their city astray, and said, 'Let us go and worship other gods,' which you have not known,
05Dt 13:14 you are to inquire, investigate, and interrogate thoroughly. If the report turns out to be true that this detestable thing has happened among you,
05Dt 13:15 you must strike down the inhabitants of that city with the sword. Completely destroy everyone in it as well as its livestock with the sword.
05Dt 13:16 You are to gather all its spoil in the middle of the city square and completely burn up the city and all its spoil for the LORD your God. The city must remain a mound of ruins forever; it is not to be rebuilt.
05Dt 13:17 Nothing set apart for destruction is to remain in your hand, so that the LORD will turn from His burning anger and grant you mercy, show you compassion, and multiply you as He swore to your fathers.
05Dt 13:18 This [will occur] if you obey the LORD your God, keeping all His commands I am giving you today, doing what is right in the sight of the LORD your God.
05Dt 14:1 "You are sons of the LORD your God; do not cut yourselves or make a bald spot on your head on behalf of the dead,
05Dt 14:2 for you are a holy people belonging to the LORD your God. The LORD has chosen you to be His special people out of all the peoples on the face of the earth.
05Dt 14:3 "You must not eat any detestable thing.
05Dt 14:4 These are the animals you may eat: the ox, the sheep, the goat,
05Dt 14:5 the deer, the gazelle, the roe deer, the wild goat, the ibex, the antelope, and the mountain sheep.
05Dt 14:6 You may eat any animal that has hooves divided in two and chews the cud.
05Dt 14:7 But among the ones that chew the cud or have divided hooves, you are not to eat these: the camel, the hare, and the hyrax, though they chew the cud, they do not have hooves-- they are unclean for you;
05Dt 14:8 and the pig, though it has hooves, it does not [chew] the cud-- it is unclean for you. You must not eat their meat or touch their carcasses.
05Dt 14:9 "You may eat everything from the water that has fins and scales,
05Dt 14:10 but you may not eat anything that does not have fins and scales-- it is unclean for you.
05Dt 14:11 "You may eat every clean bird,
05Dt 14:12 but these are the ones you may not eat: the eagle, the bearded vulture, the black vulture,
05Dt 14:13 the kite, the various kinds of falcon,
05Dt 14:14 every kind of raven,
05Dt 14:15 the ostrich, the short-eared owl, the gull, the various kinds of hawk,
05Dt 14:16 the little owl, the long-eared owl, the white owl,
05Dt 14:17 the desert owl, the osprey, the cormorant,
05Dt 14:18 the stork, the various kinds of heron, the hoopoe, and the bat.
05Dt 14:19 All winged insects are unclean for you; they may not be eaten.
05Dt 14:20 But you may eat every clean flying creature.
05Dt 14:21 "You are not to eat any carcass; you may give it to a resident alien within your gates, and he may eat it, or you may sell it to a foreigner. For you are a holy people belonging to the LORD your God. You must not boil a young goat in its mother's milk.
05Dt 14:22 "Each year you are to set aside a tenth of all the produce grown in your fields.
05Dt 14:23 You are to eat a tenth of your grain, new wine, and oil, and the firstborn of your herd and flock, in the presence of the LORD your God at the place where He chooses to have His name dwell, so that you will always learn to fear the LORD your God.
05Dt 14:24 But if the distance is too great for you to carry it, since the place where the LORD your God chooses to put His name is too far away from you and since the LORD your God has blessed you,
05Dt 14:25 then exchange it for money, take the money in your hand, and go to the place the LORD your God chooses.
05Dt 14:26 You may spend the money on anything you want: cattle, sheep, wine, beer, or anything you desire. You are to feast there in the presence of the LORD your God and rejoice with your family.
05Dt 14:27 Do not forget the Levite within your gates, since he has no portion or inheritance among you.
05Dt 14:28 "At the end of [every] three years, bring a tenth of all your produce for that year and store [it] within your gates.
05Dt 14:29 Then the Levite, who has no portion or inheritance among you, the foreign resident, fatherless, and widow within your gates may come, eat, and be satisfied. And the LORD your God will bless you in all the work of your hands that you do.
05Dt 15:1 "At the end of [every] seven years you must cancel debts.
05Dt 15:2 This is how to cancel debt: Every creditor is to cancel what he has lent his neighbor. He is not to collect [anything] from his neighbor or brother, because the LORD's release of debts has been proclaimed.
05Dt 15:3 You may collect [something] from a foreigner, but you must forgive whatever your brother owes you.
05Dt 15:4 "There will be no poor among you, however, because the LORD is certain to bless you in the land the LORD your God is giving you to possess as an inheritance--
05Dt 15:5 if only you obey the LORD your God and are careful to follow every one of these commands I am giving you today.
05Dt 15:6 When the LORD your God blesses you as He has promised you, you will lend to many nations but not borrow; you will rule over many nations, but they will not rule over you.
05Dt 15:7 "If there is a poor person among you, one of your brothers within any of your gates in the land the LORD your God is giving you, you must not be hardhearted or tightfisted toward your poor brother.
05Dt 15:8 Instead, you are to open your hand to him and freely loan him enough for whatever need he has.
05Dt 15:9 Be careful that there isn't this wicked thought in your heart, 'The seventh year, the year of canceling debts, is near,' and you are stingy toward your poor brother and give him [nothing]. He will cry out to the LORD against you, and you will be guilty.
05Dt 15:10 Give to him, and don't have a stingy heart when you give, and because of this the LORD your God will bless you in all your work and in everything you do.
05Dt 15:11 For there will never cease to be poor people in the land; that is why I am commanding you, 'You must willingly open your hand to your afflicted and poor brother in your land.'
05Dt 15:12 "If your fellow Hebrew, a man or woman, is sold to you and serves you six years, you must set him free in the seventh year.
05Dt 15:13 When you set him free, do not send him away empty-handed.
05Dt 15:14 Give generously to him from your flock, your threshing floor, and your winepress. You are to give him whatever the LORD your God has blessed you with.
05Dt 15:15 Remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt and the LORD your God redeemed you; that is why I am giving you this command today.
05Dt 15:16 But if your slave says to you, 'I don't want to leave you,' because he loves you and your family, and is well off with you,
05Dt 15:17 take an awl and pierce through his ear into the door, and he will become your slave for life. Also treat your female slave the same way.
05Dt 15:18 Do not regard it as a hardship when you set him free, because he worked for you six years-- worth twice the wages of a hired hand. Then the LORD your God will bless you in everything you do.
05Dt 15:19 "You must consecrate to the LORD your God every firstborn male produced by your herd and flock. You are not to put the firstborn of your oxen to work or shear the firstborn of your flock.
05Dt 15:20 Each year you and your family are to eat it before the LORD your God in the place the LORD chooses.
05Dt 15:21 But if there is a defect in the animal, if it is lame or blind or has any serious defect, you must not sacrifice it to the LORD your God.
05Dt 15:22 Eat it within your gates; both the unclean person and the clean [may eat it], as though it were a gazelle or deer.
05Dt 15:23 But you must not eat its blood; pour it on the ground like water.
05Dt 16:1 "Observe the month of Abib and celebrate the Passover to the LORD your God, because the LORD your God brought you out of Egypt by night in the month of Abib.
05Dt 16:2 Sacrifice to the LORD your God a Passover animal from the herd or flock in the place where the LORD chooses to have His name dwell.
05Dt 16:3 You must not eat leavened bread with it. For seven days you are to eat unleavened bread with it, the bread of hardship-- because you left the land of Egypt in a hurry-- so that you may remember for the rest of your life the day you left the land of Egypt.
05Dt 16:4 No yeast is to be found anywhere in your territory for seven days, and none of the meat you sacrifice in the evening of the first day is to remain until morning.
05Dt 16:5 You are not to sacrifice the Passover animal in any of the towns the LORD your God is giving you.
05Dt 16:6 You must only sacrifice the Passover animal at the place where the LORD your God chooses to have His name dwell. [Do this] in the evening as the sun sets at the [same] time [of day] you departed from Egypt.
05Dt 16:7 You are to cook and eat [it] in the place the LORD your God chooses, and you are to return to your tents in the morning.
05Dt 16:8 You must eat unleavened bread for six days. On the seventh day there is to be a solemn assembly to the LORD your God, and you must not do any work.
05Dt 16:9 "You are to count seven weeks, counting the weeks from the time the sickle is first [put] to the standing grain.
05Dt 16:10 You are to celebrate the Festival of Weeks to the LORD your God with a freewill offering that you give in proportion to how the LORD your God has blessed you.
05Dt 16:11 Rejoice before the LORD your God in the place where He chooses to have His name dwell-- you, your son and daughter, your male and female slave, the Levite within your gates, as well as the foreign resident, the fatherless, and the widow among you.
05Dt 16:12 Remember that you were slaves in Egypt; carefully follow these statutes.
05Dt 16:13 "You are to celebrate the Festival of Booths for seven days when you have gathered in [everything] from your threshing floor and winepress.
05Dt 16:14 Rejoice during your festival-- you, your son and daughter, your male and female slave, as well as the Levite, the foreign resident, the fatherless, and the widow within your gates.
05Dt 16:15 You are to hold a seven-day festival for the LORD your God in the place He chooses, because the LORD your God will bless you in all your produce and in all the work of your hands, and you will have abundant joy.
05Dt 16:16 "All your males are to appear three times a year before the LORD your God in the place He chooses: at the Festival of Unleavened Bread, the Festival of Weeks, and the Festival of Booths. No one is to appear before the LORD empty-handed.
05Dt 16:17 Everyone [must appear] with a gift suited to his means, according to the blessing the LORD your God has given you.
05Dt 16:18 "Appoint judges and officials for your tribes in all your towns the LORD your God is giving you. They are to judge the people with righteous judgment.
05Dt 16:19 Do not deny justice or show partiality [to anyone]. Do not accept a bribe, for it blinds the eyes of the wise and twists the words of the righteous.
05Dt 16:20 Pursue justice and justice alone, so that you will live and possess the land the LORD your God is giving you.
05Dt 16:21 "Do not set up an Asherah of any kind of wood next to the altar you will build for the LORD your God,
05Dt 16:22 and do not set up a sacred pillar; the LORD your God hates them.
05Dt 17:1 "You must not sacrifice to the LORD your God an ox or sheep with a defect or any serious flaw, for that is detestable to the LORD your God.
05Dt 17:2 "If a man or woman among you in one of your towns that the LORD your God will give you is discovered doing evil in the sight of the LORD your God and violating His covenant
05Dt 17:3 and has gone to worship other gods by bowing down to the sun, moon, or all the stars in the sky-- which I have forbidden--
05Dt 17:4 and if you are told or hear [about it], you must investigate it thoroughly. If the report turns out to be true that this detestable thing has happened in Israel,
05Dt 17:5 you must bring out to your gates that man or woman who has done this evil thing and stone them to death.
05Dt 17:6 The one condemned to die is to be executed on the testimony of two or three witnesses. No one is to be executed on the testimony of a single witness.
05Dt 17:7 The witnesses' hands are to be the first in putting him to death, and after that, the hands of all the people. You must purge the evil from you.
05Dt 17:8 "If a case is too difficult for you-- concerning bloodshed, lawsuits, or assaults-- cases disputed at your gates, you must go up to the place the LORD your God chooses.
05Dt 17:9 You are to go to the Levitical priests and to the judge who presides at that time. Ask, and they will give you a verdict in the case.
05Dt 17:10 You must abide by the verdict they give you at the place the LORD chooses. Be careful to do exactly as they instruct you.
05Dt 17:11 You must abide by the instruction they give you and the verdict they announce to you. Do not turn to the right or the left from the decision they declare to you.
05Dt 17:12 The person who acts arrogantly, refusing to listen either to the priest who stands there serving the LORD your God or to the judge, must die. You must purge the evil from Israel.
05Dt 17:13 Then all the people will hear [about it], be afraid, and no longer behave arrogantly.
05Dt 17:14 "When you enter the land the LORD your God is giving you, take possession of it, live in it, and say, 'We want to appoint a king over us like all the nations around us,'
05Dt 17:15 you are to appoint over you the king the LORD your God chooses. Appoint a king from your brothers. You are not to set a foreigner over you, or one who is not of your people.
05Dt 17:16 However, he must not acquire many horses for himself or send the people back to Egypt to acquire many horses, for the LORD has told you, 'You are never to go back that way again.'
05Dt 17:17 He must not acquire many wives for himself so that his heart won't go astray. He must not acquire very large amounts of silver and gold for himself.
05Dt 17:18 When he is seated on his royal throne, he is to write a copy of this instruction for himself on a scroll in the presence of the Levitical priests.
05Dt 17:19 It is to remain with him, and he is to read from it all the days of his life, so that he may learn to fear the LORD his God, to observe all the words of this instruction, and to do these statutes.
05Dt 17:20 Then his heart will not be exalted above his countrymen, he will not turn from this command to the right or the left, and he and his sons will continue ruling many years over Israel.
05Dt 18:1 "The Levitical priests, the whole tribe of Levi, will have no portion or inheritance with Israel. They will eat the LORD's fire offerings; that is their inheritance.
05Dt 18:2 Although Levi has no inheritance among his brothers, the LORD is his inheritance, as He promised him.
05Dt 18:3 This is the priests' share from the people who offer a sacrifice, whether it is an ox, a sheep, or a goat; the priests are to be given the shoulder, jaws, and stomach.
05Dt 18:4 You are to give him the firstfruits of your grain, new wine, and oil, and the first sheared [wool] of your flock.
05Dt 18:5 For the LORD your God has chosen him and his sons from all your tribes to stand and minister in the LORD's name from now on.
05Dt 18:6 When a Levite leaves one of your towns where he lives in Israel and wants to go to the place the LORD chooses,
05Dt 18:7 he may serve in the name of the LORD his God like all his fellow Levites who minister there in the presence of the LORD.
05Dt 18:8 They will eat equal portions besides what he has received from the sale of the family estate.
05Dt 18:9 "When you enter the land the LORD your God is giving you, do not imitate the detestable customs of those nations.
05Dt 18:10 No one among you is to make his son or daughter pass through the fire, practice divination, tell fortunes, interpret omens, practice sorcery,
05Dt 18:11 cast spells, consult a medium or a familiar spirit, or inquire of the dead.
05Dt 18:12 Everyone who does these things is detestable to the LORD, and the LORD your God is driving out the nations before you because of these detestable things.
05Dt 18:13 You must be blameless before the LORD your God.
05Dt 18:14 Though these nations you are about to drive out listen to fortune-tellers and diviners, the LORD your God has not permitted you to do this.
05Dt 18:15 "The LORD your God will raise up for you a prophet like me from among your own brothers. You must listen to him.
05Dt 18:16 This is what you requested from the LORD your God at Horeb on the day of the assembly when you said, 'Let us not continue to hear the voice of the LORD our God or see this great fire any longer, so that we will not die!'
05Dt 18:17 Then the LORD said to me, 'They have spoken well.
05Dt 18:18 I will raise up for them a prophet like you from among their brothers. I will put My words in his mouth, and he will tell them everything I command him.
05Dt 18:19 I will hold accountable whoever does not listen to My words that he speaks in My name.
05Dt 18:20 But the prophet who dares to speak in My name a message I have not commanded him to speak, or who speaks in the name of other gods-- that prophet must die.'
05Dt 18:21 You may say to yourself, 'How can we recognize a message the LORD has not spoken?'
05Dt 18:22 When a prophet speaks in the LORD's name, and the message does not come true or is not fulfilled, that is a message the LORD has not spoken. The prophet has spoken it presumptuously. Do not be afraid of him.
05Dt 19:1 "When the LORD your God annihilates the nations whose land He is giving you, so that you drive them out and live in their cities and houses,
05Dt 19:2 you are to set apart three cities for yourselves within the land the LORD your God is giving you to possess.
05Dt 19:3 You are to determine the distances and divide the land the LORD your God is granting you as an inheritance into three regions, so that anyone who commits manslaughter can flee to these cities.
05Dt 19:4 "Here is the law concerning a case of someone who kills a person and flees there to save his life, having killed his neighbor accidentally without previously hating him:
05Dt 19:5 If he goes into the forest with his neighbor to cut timber, and his hand swings the ax to chop down a tree, but the blade flies off the handle and strikes his neighbor so that he dies, that person may flee to one of these cities and live.
05Dt 19:6 Otherwise, the avenger of blood in the heat of his anger might pursue the one who committed manslaughter, overtake him because the distance is great, and strike him dead. Yet he did not deserve to die, since he did not previously hate his neighbor.
05Dt 19:7 This is why I am commanding you to set apart three cities for yourselves.
05Dt 19:8 If the LORD your God enlarges your territory as He swore to your fathers, and gives you all the land He promised to give them--
05Dt 19:9 provided you keep every one of these commands I am giving you today and follow them, loving the LORD your God and walking in His ways at all times-- you are to add three more cities to these three.
05Dt 19:10 In this way, innocent blood will not be shed, and you will not become guilty of bloodshed in the land the LORD your God is giving you as an inheritance.
05Dt 19:11 But if someone hates his neighbor, lies in ambush for him, attacks him, and strikes him fatally, and flees to one of these cities,
05Dt 19:12 the elders of his city must send [for him], take him from there, and hand him over to the avenger of blood and he will die.
05Dt 19:13 You must not look on him with pity but purge from Israel the guilt of shedding innocent blood, and you will prosper.
05Dt 19:14 "You must not move your neighbor's boundary marker, established at the start in the inheritance you will receive in the land the LORD your God is giving you to possess.
05Dt 19:15 "One witness cannot establish any wrongdoing or sin against a person, whatever that person has done. A fact must be established by the testimony of two or three witnesses.
05Dt 19:16 "If a malicious witness testifies against someone accusing him of a crime,
05Dt 19:17 the two people in the dispute must stand in the presence of the LORD before the priests and judges in authority at the time.
05Dt 19:18 The judges are to make a careful investigation, and if the witness turns out to be a liar who has falsely accused his brother,
05Dt 19:19 you must do to him as he intended to do to his brother. You must purge the evil from you.
05Dt 19:20 Then everyone else will hear and be afraid, and they will never again do anything evil like this among you.
05Dt 19:21 You must not show pity: life for life, eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, and foot for foot.
05Dt 20:1 "When you go out to war against your enemies and see horses, chariots, and an army larger than yours, do not be afraid of them, for the LORD your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, is with you.
05Dt 20:2 When you are about to engage in battle, the priest is to come forward and address the army.
05Dt 20:3 He is to say to them: 'Listen, Israel: Today you are about to engage in battle with your enemies. Do not be fainthearted. Do not be afraid, alarmed, or terrified because of them.
05Dt 20:4 For the LORD your God is the One who goes with you to fight for you against your enemies to give you victory.'
05Dt 20:5 "The officers are to address the army, 'Has any man built a new house and not dedicated it? Let him leave and return home. Otherwise, he may die in battle and another man dedicate it.
05Dt 20:6 Has any man planted a vineyard and not begun to enjoy its fruit? Let him leave and return home. Otherwise he may die in battle and another man enjoy its fruit.
05Dt 20:7 Has any man become engaged to a woman and not married her? Let him leave and return home. Otherwise he may die in battle and another man marry her.'
05Dt 20:8 The officers will continue to address the army and say, 'Is there any man who is afraid or fainthearted? Let him leave and return home, so that his brothers' hearts won't melt like his own.'
05Dt 20:9 When the officers have finished addressing the army, they will appoint military commanders to lead it.
05Dt 20:10 "When you approach a city to fight against it, you must make an offer of peace.
05Dt 20:11 If it accepts your offer of peace and opens [its gates] to you, all the people found in it will become forced laborers for you and serve you.
05Dt 20:12 However, if it does not make peace with you but wages war against you, lay siege to it.
05Dt 20:13 When the LORD your God hands it over to you, you must strike down all its males with the sword.
05Dt 20:14 But you may take the women, children, animals, and whatever else is in the city-- all its spoil-- as plunder. You may enjoy the spoil of your enemies that the LORD your God has given you.
05Dt 20:15 This is how you are to treat all the cities that are far away from you and are not among the cities of these nations.
05Dt 20:16 However, you must not let any living thing survive among the cities of these people the LORD your God is giving you as an inheritance.
05Dt 20:17 You must completely destroy them-- the Hittite, Amorite, Canaanite, Perizzite, Hivite, and Jebusite-- as the LORD your God has commanded you,
05Dt 20:18 so that they won't teach you to do all the detestable things they do for their gods, and you sin against the LORD your God.
05Dt 20:19 "When you lay siege to a city for a long time, fighting against it in order to capture it, you must not destroy its trees by putting an ax to them, because you can get food from them. You must not cut them down. Are trees of the field human, to come under siege by you?
05Dt 20:20 But you may destroy the trees that you know do not produce food. You may cut them down to build siege works against the city that is waging war with you, until it falls.
05Dt 21:1 "If a murder victim is found lying in a field in the land the LORD your God is giving you to possess, and it is not known who killed him,
05Dt 21:2 your elders and judges must come out and measure [the distance] from the victim to the nearby cities.
05Dt 21:3 The elders of the city nearest to the victim are to get a cow that has not been yoked or used for work.
05Dt 21:4 The elders of that city will bring the cow down to a continually flowing stream, to a place not tilled or sown, and they will break the cow's neck there by the stream.
05Dt 21:5 Then the priests, the sons of Levi, will come forward, for the LORD your God has chosen them to serve Him and pronounce blessings in the LORD's name, and they are to give a ruling in every dispute and [case of] assault.
05Dt 21:6 All the elders of the city nearest to the victim will wash their hands by the stream over the heifer whose neck has been broken.
05Dt 21:7 They will declare, 'Our hands did not shed this blood; our eyes did not see [it].
05Dt 21:8 LORD, forgive Your people Israel You redeemed, and do not hold the shedding of innocent blood against them.' Then they will be absolved of responsibility for bloodshed.
05Dt 21:9 You must purge from yourselves the guilt of shedding innocent blood, for you will be doing what is right in the LORD's sight.
05Dt 21:10 "When you go to war against your enemies and the LORD your God hands them over to you and you take some of them prisoner, and
05Dt 21:11 if you see a beautiful woman among the captives, desire her, and want to take her as your wife,
05Dt 21:12 you are to bring her into your house. She must shave her head, trim her nails,
05Dt 21:13 remove the clothes she was wearing when she was taken prisoner, live in your house, and mourn for her father and mother a full month. After that, you may have sexual relations with her and be her husband, and she will be your wife.
05Dt 21:14 Then if you are not satisfied with her, you are to let her go where she wants, but you must not sell her for money or treat her as merchandise, because you have humiliated her.
05Dt 21:15 "If a man has two wives, one loved and the other unloved, and both the loved and the unloved bear him sons, and if the unloved wife has the firstborn son,
05Dt 21:16 when that man gives what he has to his sons as an inheritance, he is not to show favoritism to the son of the loved [wife] as his firstborn over the firstborn of the unloved wife.
05Dt 21:17 He must acknowledge the firstborn, the son of the unloved wife, by giving him a double portion of everything that belongs to him, for he is the firstfruits of his virility; he has the rights of the firstborn.
05Dt 21:18 "If a man has a stubborn and rebellious son who does not obey his father or mother and doesn't listen to them even after they discipline him,
05Dt 21:19 his father and mother must take hold of him and bring him to the elders of his city, to the gate of his hometown.
05Dt 21:20 They will say to the elders of his city, 'This son of ours is stubborn and rebellious; he doesn't obey us. He's a glutton and a drunkard.'
05Dt 21:21 Then all the men of his city will stone him to death. You must purge the evil from you, and all Israel will hear and be afraid.
05Dt 21:22 "If anyone is found guilty of an offense deserving the death penalty and is executed, and you hang his body on a tree,
05Dt 21:23 you are not to leave his corpse on the tree overnight but are to bury him that day, for anyone hung [on a tree] is under God's curse. You must not defile the land the LORD your God is giving you as an inheritance.
05Dt 22:1 "If you see your brother's ox or sheep straying, you must not ignore it; make sure you return it to your brother.
05Dt 22:2 If your brother does not live near you or you don't know him, you are to bring the animal to your home to remain with you until your brother comes looking for it; then you can return it to him.
05Dt 22:3 Do the same for his donkey, his garment, or anything your brother has lost and you have found. You must not ignore [it].
05Dt 22:4 If you see your brother's donkey or ox fallen down on the road, you must not ignore it; you must help him lift it up.
05Dt 22:5 "A woman is not to wear male clothing, and a man is not to put on a woman's garment, for everyone who does these things is detestable to the LORD your God.
05Dt 22:6 "If you come across a bird's nest with chicks or eggs, either in a tree or on the ground along the road, and the mother is sitting on the chicks or eggs, you must not take the mother along with the young.
05Dt 22:7 You may take the young for yourself, but be sure to let the mother go free, so that you may prosper and live long.
05Dt 22:8 If you build a new house, make a railing around your roof, so that you don't bring bloodguilt on your house if someone falls from it.
05Dt 22:9 Do not plant your vineyard with two types of seed; otherwise, the entire harvest, both the crop you plant and the produce of the vineyard, will be defiled.
05Dt 22:10 Do not plow with an ox and a donkey together.
05Dt 22:11 Do not wear clothes made of both wool and linen.
05Dt 22:12 Make tassels on the four corners of the outer garment you wear.
05Dt 22:13 "If a man marries a woman, has sexual relations with her, and comes to hate her,
05Dt 22:14 and accuses [her] of shameful conduct, and gives her a bad name, saying, 'I married this woman and was intimate with her, but I didn't find [any] evidence of her virginity,'
05Dt 22:15 the young woman's father and mother will take the evidence of her virginity and bring [it] to the city elders at the gate.
05Dt 22:16 The young woman's father will say to the elders, 'I gave my daughter to this man as a wife, but he hates her.
05Dt 22:17 He has accused her of shameful conduct, saying: 'I didn't find [any] evidence of your daughter's virginity, but here is the evidence of my daughter's virginity.' They will spread out the cloth before the city elders.
05Dt 22:18 Then the elders of that city will take the man and punish him.
05Dt 22:19 They will also fine him 100 silver [shekels] and give [them] to the young woman's father, because that man gave an Israelite virgin a bad name. She will remain his wife; he cannot divorce her as long as he lives.
05Dt 22:20 But if this accusation is true and no evidence of the young woman's virginity is found,
05Dt 22:21 they will bring the woman to the door of her father's house, and the men of her city will stone her to death. For she has committed an outrage in Israel by being promiscuous in her father's house. You must purge the evil from you.
05Dt 22:22 "If a man is discovered having sexual relations with [another] man's wife, both the man who had sex with the woman and the woman must die. You must purge the evil from Israel.
05Dt 22:23 If there is a young woman who is a virgin engaged to a man, and [another] man encounters her in the city and has sex with her,
05Dt 22:24 you must take the two of them out to the gate of that city and stone them to death-- the young woman because she did not cry out in the city and the man because he has violated his neighbor's fianc?. You must purge the evil from you.
05Dt 22:25 But if the man encounters the engaged woman in the open country, and he seizes and rapes her, only the man who raped her must die.
05Dt 22:26 Do nothing to the young woman, because she is not guilty of an offense deserving death. This case is just like one in which a man attacks his neighbor and murders him.
05Dt 22:27 When he found her in the field, the engaged woman cried out, but there was no one to rescue her.
05Dt 22:28 If a man encounters a young woman, a virgin who is not engaged, takes hold of her and rapes her, and they are discovered,
05Dt 22:29 the man who raped her must give the young woman's father 50 silver [shekels], and she must become his wife because he violated her. He cannot divorce her as long as he lives.
05Dt 22:30 "A man is not to marry his father's wife; he must not violate his father's marriage bed.
05Dt 23:1 "No man whose [testicles] have been crushed or whose penis has been cut off may enter the LORD's assembly.
05Dt 23:2 No one of illegitimate birth may enter the LORD's assembly; none of his descendants, even to the tenth generation, may enter the LORD's assembly.
05Dt 23:3 No Ammonite or Moabite may enter the LORD's assembly; none of their descendants, even to the tenth generation, may ever enter the LORD's assembly.
05Dt 23:4 This is because they did not meet you with food and water on the journey after you came out of Egypt, and because Balaam son of Beor from Pethor in Aram-naharaim was hired to curse you.
05Dt 23:5 Yet the LORD your God would not listen to Balaam, but He turned the curse into a blessing for you because the LORD your God loves you.
05Dt 23:6 Never seek peace or friendship with them as long as you live.
05Dt 23:7 Do not despise an Edomite, because he is your brother. Do not despise an Egyptian, because you were a foreign resident in his land.
05Dt 23:8 The children born to them in the third generation may enter the LORD's assembly.
05Dt 23:9 "When you are encamped against your enemies, be careful to avoid anything offensive.
05Dt 23:10 If there is a man among you who is unclean because of a bodily emission during the night, he must go outside the camp; he may not come anywhere inside the camp.
05Dt 23:11 When evening approaches, he must wash with water, and when the sun sets he may come inside the camp.
05Dt 23:12 You must have a place outside the camp and go there [to relieve yourself].
05Dt 23:13 You must have a digging tool in your equipment; when you relieve yourself, dig a hole with it and cover up your excrement.
05Dt 23:14 For the LORD your God walks throughout your camp to protect you and deliver your enemies to you; so your encampments must be holy. He must not see anything improper among you or He will turn away from you.
05Dt 23:15 "Do not return a slave to his master when he has escaped from his master to you.
05Dt 23:16 Let him live among you wherever he wants within your gates. Do not mistreat him.
05Dt 23:17 "No Israelite woman is to be a cult prostitute, and no Israelite man is to be a cult prostitute.
05Dt 23:18 Do not bring a female prostitute's wages or a male prostitute's earnings into the house of the LORD your God to fulfill any vow, because both are detestable to the LORD your God.
05Dt 23:19 "Do not charge your brother interest on money, food, or anything that can earn interest.
05Dt 23:20 You may charge a foreigner interest, but you must not charge your brother interest, so that the LORD your God may bless you in everything you do in the land you are entering to possess.
05Dt 23:21 "If you make a vow to the LORD your God, do not be slow to keep it, because He will require it of you, and it will be counted against you as sin.
05Dt 23:22 But if you refrain from making a vow, it will not be counted against you as sin.
05Dt 23:23 Be careful to do whatever comes from your lips, because you have freely vowed what you promised to the LORD your God.
05Dt 23:24 "When you enter your neighbor's vineyard, you may eat as many grapes as you want until you are full, but you must not put [any] in your container.
05Dt 23:25 When you enter your neighbor's standing grain, you may pluck heads of grain with your hand, but you must not put a sickle to your neighbor's grain.
05Dt 24:1 "If a man marries a woman, but she becomes displeasing to him because he finds something improper about her, he may write her a divorce certificate, hand it to her, and send her away from his house.
05Dt 24:2 If after leaving his house she goes and becomes another man's wife,
05Dt 24:3 and the second man hates her, writes her a divorce certificate, hands it to her, and sends her away from his house or if he dies,
05Dt 24:4 the first husband who sent her away may not marry her again after she has been defiled, because that would be detestable to the LORD. You must not bring guilt on the land the LORD your God is giving you as an inheritance.
05Dt 24:5 "When a man takes a bride, he must not go out with the army or be liable for any duty. He is free [to stay] at home for one year, so that he can bring joy to the wife he has married.
05Dt 24:6 "Do not take a pair of millstones or an upper millstone as security for a debt, because that is like taking a life as security.
05Dt 24:7 "If a man is discovered kidnapping one of his Israelite brothers, whether he treats him as a slave or sells him, the kidnapper must die. You must purge the evil from you.
05Dt 24:8 "Be careful in a case of infectious skin disease, following carefully everything the Levitical priests instruct you to do. Be careful to do as I have commanded them.
05Dt 24:9 Remember what the LORD your God did to Miriam on the journey after you left Egypt.
05Dt 24:10 "When you make a loan of any kind to your neighbor, do not enter his house to collect what he offers as security.
05Dt 24:11 You must stand outside while the man you are making the loan to brings the security out to you.
05Dt 24:12 If he is a poor man, you must not sleep in [the garment] he has given as security.
05Dt 24:13 Be sure to return it to him at sunset. Then he will sleep in it and bless you, and this will be counted as righteousness to you before the LORD your God.
05Dt 24:14 "Do not oppress a hired hand who is poor and needy, whether one of your brothers or one of the foreigners residing within a town in your land.
05Dt 24:15 You are to pay him his wages each day before the sun sets, because he is poor and depends on them. Otherwise he will cry out to the LORD against you, and you will be held guilty.
05Dt 24:16 "Fathers are not to be put to death for [their] children or children for [their] fathers; each person will be put to death for his own sin.
05Dt 24:17 Do not deny justice to a foreign resident [or] fatherless child, and do not take a widow's garment as security.
05Dt 24:18 Remember that you were a slave in Egypt, and the LORD your God redeemed you from there. Therefore I am commanding you to do this.
05Dt 24:19 "When you reap the harvest in your field, and you forget a sheaf in the field, do not go back to get it. It is to be left for the foreign resident, the fatherless, and the widow, so that the LORD your God may bless you in all the work of your hands.
05Dt 24:20 When you knock down the fruit from your olive tree, you must not go over the branches again. What remains will be for the foreign resident, the fatherless, and the widow.
05Dt 24:21 When you gather the grapes of your vineyard, you must not glean what is left. What remains will be for the foreign resident, the fatherless, and the widow.
05Dt 24:22 Remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt. Therefore I am commanding you to do this.
05Dt 25:1 "If there is a dispute between men, they are to go to court, and the judges will hear their case. They will clear the innocent and condemn the guilty.
05Dt 25:2 If the guilty party deserves to be flogged, the judge will make him lie down and be flogged in his presence with the number [of lashes] appropriate for his crime.
05Dt 25:3 He may be flogged with 40 lashes, but no more. Otherwise, if he is flogged with more lashes than these, your brother will be degraded in your sight.
05Dt 25:4 "Do not muzzle an ox while it treads out grain.
05Dt 25:5 "When brothers live on the same property and one of them dies without a son, the wife of the dead man may not marry a stranger outside [the family]. Her brother-in-law is to take her as his wife, have sexual relations with her, and perform the duty of a brother-in-law for her.
05Dt 25:6 The first son she bears will carry on the name of the dead brother, so his name will not be blotted out from Israel.
05Dt 25:7 But if the man doesn't want to marry his sister-in-law, she must go to the elders at the [city] gate and say, 'My brother-in-law refuses to preserve his brother's name in Israel. He isn't willing to perform the duty of a brother-in-law for me.'
05Dt 25:8 The elders of his city will summon him and speak with him. If he persists and says, 'I don't want to marry her,'
05Dt 25:9 then his sister-in-law will go up to him in the sight of the elders, remove his sandal from his foot, and spit in his face. Then she will declare, 'This is what is done to a man who will not build up his brother's house.'
05Dt 25:10 And his [family] name in Israel will be called 'The house of the man whose sandal was removed.'
05Dt 25:11 "If two men are fighting with each other, and the wife of one steps in to rescue her husband from the one striking him, and she puts out her hand and grabs his genitals,
05Dt 25:12 you are to cut off her hand. You must not show pity.
05Dt 25:13 "You must not have two different weights in your bag, one heavy and one light.
05Dt 25:14 You must not have two differing dry measures in your house, a larger and a smaller.
05Dt 25:15 You must have a full and honest weight, a full and honest dry measure, so that you may live long in the land the LORD your God is giving you.
05Dt 25:16 For everyone who does such things and acts unfairly is detestable to the LORD your God.
05Dt 25:17 "Remember what the Amalekites did to you on the journey after you left Egypt.
05Dt 25:18 They met you along the way and attacked all your stragglers from behind when you were tired and weary. They did not fear God.
05Dt 25:19 When the LORD your God gives you rest from all the enemies around you in the land the LORD your God is giving you to possess as an inheritance, blot out the memory of Amalek from under heaven. Do not forget.
05Dt 26:1 "When you enter the land the LORD your God is giving you as an inheritance, and you take possession of it and live in it,
05Dt 26:2 you must take some of the first of all the soil's produce that you harvest from the land the LORD your God is giving you and put [it] in a container. Then go to the place where the LORD your God chooses to have His name dwell.
05Dt 26:3 When you come before the priest who is serving at that time, you must say to him, 'Today I acknowledge to the LORD your God that I have entered the land the LORD swore to our fathers to give us.'
05Dt 26:4 "Then the priest will take the container from your hand and place it before the altar of the LORD your God.
05Dt 26:5 You are to respond by saying in the presence of the LORD your God: My father was a wandering Aramean. He went down to Egypt with a few people and lived there. There he became a great, powerful, and populous nation.
05Dt 26:6 But the Egyptians mistreated and afflicted us, and forced us to do hard labor.
05Dt 26:7 So we called out to the LORD, the God of our fathers, and the LORD heard our cry and saw our misery, hardship, and oppression.
05Dt 26:8 Then the LORD brought us out of Egypt with a strong hand and an outstretched arm, with terrifying power, and with signs and wonders.
05Dt 26:9 He led us to this place and gave us this land, a land flowing with milk and honey.
05Dt 26:10 I have now brought the first of the land's produce that You, LORD, have given me. You will then place the container before the LORD your God and bow down to Him.
05Dt 26:11 You, the Levite, and the foreign resident among you will rejoice in all the good things the LORD your God has given you and your household.
05Dt 26:12 "When you have finished paying all the tenth of your produce in the third year, the year of the tenth, you are to give [it] to the Levite, the foreign resident, the fatherless, and the widow, so that they may eat in your towns and be satisfied.
05Dt 26:13 Then you will say in the presence of the LORD your God: I have taken the consecrated portion out of my house; I have also given it to the Levite, the foreign resident, the fatherless, and the widow, according to all the commands You gave me. I have not violated or forgotten Your commands.
05Dt 26:14 I have not eaten any of it while in mourning, or removed any of it while unclean, or offered any of it for the dead. I have obeyed the LORD my God; I have done all You commanded me.
05Dt 26:15 Look down from Your holy dwelling, from heaven, and bless Your people Israel and the land You have given us as You swore to our fathers, a land flowing with milk and honey.
05Dt 26:16 "The LORD your God is commanding you this day to follow these statutes and ordinances. You must be careful to follow them with all your heart and all your soul.
05Dt 26:17 Today you have affirmed that the LORD is your God and that you will walk in His ways, keep His statutes, commands, and ordinances, and obey Him.
05Dt 26:18 And today the LORD has affirmed that you are His special people as He promised you, that you are to keep all His commands,
05Dt 26:19 that He will put you far above all the nations He has made in praise, fame, and glory, and that you will be a holy people to the LORD your God as He promised."
05Dt 27:1 Moses and the elders of Israel commanded the people, "Keep every command I am giving you today.
05Dt 27:2 At the time you cross the Jordan into the land the LORD your God is giving you, you must set up large stones and cover them with plaster.
05Dt 27:3 Write all the words of this law on the stones after you cross to enter the land the LORD your God is giving you, a land flowing with milk and honey, as the LORD, the God of your fathers, has promised you.
05Dt 27:4 When you have crossed the Jordan, you are to set up these stones on Mount Ebal, as I am commanding you today, and you are to cover them with plaster.
05Dt 27:5 Build an altar of stones there to the LORD your God-- you must not use any iron tool on them.
05Dt 27:6 Use uncut stones to build the altar of the LORD your God and offer burnt offerings to the LORD your God on it.
05Dt 27:7 There you are to sacrifice fellowship offerings, eat, and rejoice in the presence of the LORD your God.
05Dt 27:8 Write clearly all the words of this law on the [plastered] stones."
05Dt 27:9 Moses and the Levitical priests spoke to all Israel, "Be silent, Israel, and listen! This day you have become the people of the LORD your God.
05Dt 27:10 Obey the LORD your God and follow His commands and statutes I am giving you today."
05Dt 27:11 On that day Moses commanded the people,
05Dt 27:12 "When you have crossed the Jordan, these [tribes] will stand on Mount Gerizim to bless the people: Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Joseph, and Benjamin.
05Dt 27:13 And these [tribes] will stand on Mount Ebal to deliver the curse: Reuben, Gad, Asher, Zebulun, Dan, and Naphtali.
05Dt 27:14 The Levites will proclaim in a loud voice to every Israelite:
05Dt 27:15 'Cursed is the person who makes a carved idol or cast image, which is detestable to the LORD, the work of a craftsman, and sets [it] up in secret.' And all the people will reply, ' Amen!'
05Dt 27:16 'Cursed is the one who dishonors his father or mother.' And all the people will say, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:17 'Cursed is the one who moves his neighbor's boundary marker.' And all the people will say, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:18 'Cursed is the one who leads a blind person astray on the road.' And all the people will say, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:19 'Cursed is the one who denies justice to a foreign resident, a fatherless child, or a widow.' And all the people will say, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:20 'Cursed is the one who sleeps with his father's wife, for he has violated his father's marriage bed.' And all the people will say, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:21 'Cursed is the one who has sexual intercourse with any animal.' And all the people will say 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:22 'Cursed is the one who sleeps with his sister, whether his father's daughter or his mother's daughter.' And all the people will say, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:23 'Cursed is the one who sleeps with his mother-in-law.' And all the people will say, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:24 'Cursed is the one who kills his neighbor in secret.' And all the people will say, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:25 'Cursed is the one who accepts a bribe to kill an innocent person.' And all the people will say, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:26 'Cursed is anyone who does not put the words of this law into practice.' And all the people will say, 'Amen!'
05Dt 28:1 "Now if you faithfully obey the LORD your God and are careful to follow all His commands I am giving you today, the LORD your God will put you far above all the nations of the earth.
05Dt 28:2 All these blessings will come and overtake you, because you obey the LORD your God:
05Dt 28:3 You will be blessed in the city and blessed in the country.
05Dt 28:4 Your descendants will be blessed, and your soil's produce, and the offspring of your livestock, including the young of your herds and the newborn of your flocks.
05Dt 28:5 Your basket and kneading bowl will be blessed.
05Dt 28:6 You will be blessed when you come in and blessed when you go out.
05Dt 28:7 "The LORD will cause the enemies who rise up against you to be defeated before you. They will march out against you from one direction but flee from you in seven directions.
05Dt 28:8 The LORD will grant you a blessing on your storehouses and on everything you do; He will bless you in the land the LORD your God is giving you.
05Dt 28:9 The LORD will establish you as His holy people, as He swore to you, if you obey the commands of the LORD your God and walk in His ways.
05Dt 28:10 Then all the peoples of the earth will see that you are called by the LORD's name, and they will stand in awe of you.
05Dt 28:11 The LORD will make you prosper abundantly with children, the offspring of your livestock, and your soil's produce in the land the LORD swore to your fathers to give you.
05Dt 28:12 The LORD will open for you His abundant storehouse, the sky, to give your land rain in its season and to bless all the work of your hands. You will lend to many nations, but you will not borrow.
05Dt 28:13 The LORD will make you the head and not the tail; you will only move upward and never downward if you listen to the LORD your God's commands I am giving you today and are careful to follow [them].
05Dt 28:14 Do not turn aside to the right or the left from all the things I am commanding you today, and do not go after other gods to worship them.
05Dt 28:15 "But if you do not obey the LORD your God by carefully following all His commands and statutes I am giving you today, all these curses will come and overtake you:
05Dt 28:16 You will be cursed in the city and cursed in the country.
05Dt 28:17 Your basket and kneading bowl will be cursed.
05Dt 28:18 Your descendants will be cursed, and your soil's produce, the young of your herds, and the newborn of your flocks.
05Dt 28:19 You will be cursed when you come in and cursed when you go out.
05Dt 28:20 The LORD will send against you curses, confusion, and rebuke in everything you do until you are destroyed and quickly perish, because of the wickedness of your actions in abandoning Me.
05Dt 28:21 The LORD will make pestilence cling to you until He has exterminated you from the land you are entering to possess.
05Dt 28:22 The LORD will afflict you with wasting disease, fever, inflammation, burning heat, drought, blight, and mildew; these will pursue you until you perish.
05Dt 28:23 The sky above you will be bronze, and the earth beneath you iron.
05Dt 28:24 The LORD will turn the rain of your land into falling dust; it will descend on you from the sky until you are destroyed.
05Dt 28:25 The LORD will cause you to be defeated before your enemies. You will march out against them from one direction but flee from them in seven directions. You will be an object of horror to all the kingdoms of the earth.
05Dt 28:26 Your corpses will be food for all the birds of the sky and the wild animals of the land, and no one will scare them away.
05Dt 28:27 "The LORD will afflict you with the boils of Egypt, tumors, a festering rash, and scabies, from which you cannot be cured.
05Dt 28:28 The LORD will afflict you with madness, blindness, and mental confusion,
05Dt 28:29 so that at noon you will grope as a blind man gropes in the dark. You will not be successful in anything you do. You will only be oppressed and robbed continually, and no one will help [you].
05Dt 28:30 You will become engaged to a woman, but another man will rape her. You will build a house but not live in it. You will plant a vineyard but not enjoy its fruit.
05Dt 28:31 Your ox will be slaughtered before your eyes, but you will not eat any of it. Your donkey will be taken away from you and not returned to you. Your flock will be given to your enemies, and no one will help you.
05Dt 28:32 Your sons and daughters will be given to another people, while your eyes grow weary looking for them every day. But you will be powerless to do anything.
05Dt 28:33 A people you don't know will eat your soil's produce and everything you have labored for. You will only be oppressed and crushed continually.
05Dt 28:34 You will be driven mad by what you see.
05Dt 28:35 The LORD will afflict you on your knees and thighs with painful and incurable boils from the sole of your foot to the top of your head.
05Dt 28:36 "The LORD will bring you and your king that you have appointed to a nation neither you nor your fathers have known, and there you will worship other gods, of wood and stone.
05Dt 28:37 You will become an object of horror, scorn, and ridicule among all the peoples where the LORD will drive you.
05Dt 28:38 "You will sow much seed in the field but harvest little, because locusts will devour it.
05Dt 28:39 You will plant and cultivate vineyards but not drink the wine or gather [the grapes], because worms will eat them.
05Dt 28:40 You will have olives trees throughout your territory but not anoint yourself with oil, because your olives will drop off.
05Dt 28:41 You will father sons and daughters, but they will not remain yours, because they will be taken prisoner.
05Dt 28:42 Whirring insects will take possession of all your trees and your land's produce.
05Dt 28:43 The foreign resident among you will rise higher and higher above you, while you sink lower and lower.
05Dt 28:44 He will lend to you, but you won't lend to him. He will be the head, and you will be the tail.
05Dt 28:45 "All these curses will come, pursue, and overtake you until you are destroyed, since you did not obey the LORD your God and keep the commands and statutes He gave you.
05Dt 28:46 These curses will be a sign and a wonder against you and your descendants forever.
05Dt 28:47 Because you didn't serve the LORD your God with joy and a cheerful heart, even though [you had] an abundance of everything,
05Dt 28:48 you will serve your enemies the LORD will send against you, in famine, thirst, nakedness, and a lack of everything. He will place an iron yoke on your neck until He has destroyed you.
05Dt 28:49 The LORD will bring a nation from far away, from the ends of the earth, to swoop down on you like an eagle, a nation whose language you don't understand,
05Dt 28:50 a ruthless nation, showing no respect for the old and not sparing the young.
05Dt 28:51 They will eat the offspring of your livestock and your soil's produce until you are destroyed. They will leave you no grain, new wine, oil, young of your herds, or newborn of your flocks until they cause you to perish.
05Dt 28:52 They will besiege you within all your gates until your high and fortified walls, that you trust in, come down throughout your land. They will besiege you within all your gates throughout the land the LORD your God has given you.
05Dt 28:53 "You will eat your children, the flesh of your sons and daughters the LORD your God has given you during the siege and hardship your enemy imposes on you.
05Dt 28:54 The most sensitive and refined man among you will look grudgingly at his brother, the wife he embraces, and the rest of his children,
05Dt 28:55 refusing to share with any of them his children's flesh that he will eat because he has nothing left during the siege and hardship your enemy imposes on you in all your towns.
05Dt 28:56 The most sensitive and refined woman among you, who would not venture to set the sole of her foot on the ground because of her refinement and sensitivity, will begrudge the husband she embraces, her son, and her daughter,
05Dt 28:57 the afterbirth that comes out from between her legs and the children she bears, because she will secretly eat them for lack of anything [else] during the siege and hardship your enemy imposes on you within your gates.
05Dt 28:58 "If you are not careful to obey all the words of this law, which are written in this scroll, by fearing this glorious and awesome name-- Yahweh, your God--
05Dt 28:59 He will bring extraordinary plagues on you and your descendants, severe and lasting plagues, and terrible and chronic sicknesses.
05Dt 28:60 He will afflict you again with all the diseases of Egypt, which you dreaded, and they will cling to you.
05Dt 28:61 The LORD will also inflict you with every sickness and plague not recorded in the book of this law, until you are destroyed.
05Dt 28:62 Though you were as numerous as the stars of the sky, you will be left with only a few people, because you did not obey the LORD your God.
05Dt 28:63 Just as the LORD was glad to cause you to prosper and to multiply you, so He will also be glad to cause you to perish and to destroy you. You will be deported from the land you are entering to possess.
05Dt 28:64 Then the LORD will scatter you among all peoples from one end of the earth to the other, and there you will worship other gods of wood and stone, which neither you nor your fathers have known.
05Dt 28:65 You will find no peace among those nations, and there will be no resting place for the sole of your foot. There the LORD will give you a trembling heart, failing eyes, and a despondent spirit.
05Dt 28:66 Your life will hang in doubt before you. You will be in dread night and day, never certain of survival.
05Dt 28:67 In the morning you will say, 'If only it were evening!' and in the evening you will say, 'If only it were morning!'-- because of the dread you will have in your heart and because of what you will see.
05Dt 28:68 The LORD will take you back in ships to Egypt by a route that I said you would never see again. There you will sell yourselves to your enemies as male and female slaves, but no one will buy [you]."
05Dt 29:1  These are the words of the covenant the LORD commanded Moses to make with the Israelites in the land of Moab, in addition to the covenant He had made with them at Horeb.
05Dt 29:2  Moses summoned all Israel and said to them, "You have seen with your own eyes everything the LORD did in Egypt to Pharaoh, to all his officials, and to his entire land.
05Dt 29:3 You saw with your own eyes the great trials and those great signs and wonders.
05Dt 29:4 Yet to this day the LORD has not given you a mind to understand, eyes to see, or ears to hear.
05Dt 29:5 I led you 40 years in the wilderness; your clothes and the sandals on your feet did not wear out;
05Dt 29:6 you did not eat bread or drink wine or beer-- so that you might know that I am the LORD your God.
05Dt 29:7 When you reached this place, Sihon king of Heshbon and Og king of Bashan came out against us in battle, but we defeated them.
05Dt 29:8 We took their land and gave it as an inheritance to the Reubenites, the Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh.
05Dt 29:9 Therefore, observe the words of this covenant and follow them, so that you will succeed in everything you do.
05Dt 29:10 "All of you are standing today before the LORD your God-- your leaders, tribes, elders, officials, all the men of Israel,
05Dt 29:11 your children, your wives, and the foreigners in your camps who cut your wood and draw your water--
05Dt 29:12 so that you may enter into the covenant of the LORD your God, which He is making with you today, so that you may enter into His oath
05Dt 29:13 and so that He may establish you today as His people and He may be your God as He promised you and as He swore to your fathers Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.
05Dt 29:14 I am making this covenant and this oath not only with you,
05Dt 29:15 but also with those who are standing here with us today in the presence of the LORD our God and with those who are not here today.
05Dt 29:16 "Indeed, you know how we lived in the land of Egypt and passed through the nations where you traveled.
05Dt 29:17 You saw their detestable images and idols [made] of wood, stone, silver, and gold, which were among them.
05Dt 29:18 Be sure there is no man, woman, clan, or tribe among you today whose heart turns away from the LORD our God to go and worship the gods of those nations. Be sure there is no root among you bearing poisonous and bitter fruit.
05Dt 29:19 When someone hears the words of this oath, he may bless himself in his mind, thinking, 'I will have peace even though I follow my [own] stubborn heart.' This will lead to the destruction of the well-watered [land] as well as the dry [land].
05Dt 29:20 The LORD will not be willing to forgive him. Instead, His anger and jealousy will burn against that person, and every curse written in this scroll will descend on him. The LORD will blot out his name under heaven,
05Dt 29:21 and single him out for harm from all the tribes of Israel, according to all the curses of the covenant written in this book of the law.
05Dt 29:22 "Future generations of your children who follow you and the foreigner who comes from a distant country will see the plagues of the land and the sicknesses the LORD has inflicted on it.
05Dt 29:23 All its soil will be a burning waste of sulfur and salt, unsown, producing nothing, with no plant growing on it, just like the fall of Sodom and Gomorrah, Admah and Zeboiim, which the LORD demolished in His fierce anger.
05Dt 29:24 All the nations will ask, 'Why has the LORD done this to this land? Why this great outburst of anger?'
05Dt 29:25 Then people will answer, 'It is because they abandoned the covenant of the LORD, the God of their fathers, which He had made with them when He brought them out of the land of Egypt.
05Dt 29:26 They began to worship other gods, bowing down to gods they had not known-- gods that the LORD had not permitted them [to worship].
05Dt 29:27 Therefore the LORD's anger burned against this land, and He brought every curse written in this book on it.
05Dt 29:28 The LORD uprooted them from their land in [His] anger, fury, and great wrath, and threw them into another land where they are today.'
05Dt 29:29 The hidden things belong to the LORD our God, but the revealed things belong to us and our children forever, so that we may follow all the words of this law.
05Dt 30:1 "When all these things happen to you-- the blessings and curses I have set before you-- and you come to your senses [while you are] in all the nations where the LORD your God has driven you,
05Dt 30:2 and you and your children return to the LORD your God and obey Him with all your heart and all your soul by doing everything I am giving you today,
05Dt 30:3 then He will restore your fortunes, have compassion on you, and gather you again from all the peoples where the LORD your God has scattered you.
05Dt 30:4 Even if your exiles are at the ends of the earth, He will gather you and bring you back from there.
05Dt 30:5 The LORD your God will bring you into the land your fathers possessed, and you will take possession of it. He will cause you to prosper and multiply you more than [He did] your fathers.
05Dt 30:6 The LORD your God will circumcise your heart and the hearts of your descendants, and you will love Him with all your heart and all your soul, so that you will live.
05Dt 30:7 The LORD your God will put all these curses on your enemies who hate and persecute you.
05Dt 30:8 Then you will again obey Him and follow all His commands I am giving you today.
05Dt 30:9 The LORD your God will make you prosper abundantly in all the work of your hands with children, the offspring of your livestock, and your soil's produce. Indeed, the LORD will again delight in your prosperity, as He delighted in that of your fathers,
05Dt 30:10 when you obey the LORD your God by keeping His commands and statutes that are written in this book of the law and return to Him with all your heart and all your soul.
05Dt 30:11 "This command that I give you today is certainly not too difficult or beyond your reach.
05Dt 30:12 It is not in heaven, so that you have to ask, 'Who will go up to heaven, get it for us, and proclaim it to us so that we may follow it?'
05Dt 30:13 And it is not across the sea, so that you have to ask, 'Who will cross the sea, get it for us, and proclaim it to us so that we may follow it?'
05Dt 30:14 But the message is very near you, in your mouth and in your heart, so that you may follow it.
05Dt 30:15 See, today I have set before you life and prosperity, death and adversity.
05Dt 30:16 For I am commanding you today to love the LORD your God, to walk in His ways, and to keep His commands, statutes, and ordinances, so that you may live and multiply, and the LORD your God may bless you in the land you are entering to possess.
05Dt 30:17 But if your heart turns away and you do not listen and you are led astray to bow down to other gods and worship them,
05Dt 30:18 I tell you today that you will certainly perish and will not live long in the land you are entering to possess across the Jordan.
05Dt 30:19 I call heaven and earth as witnesses against you today that I have set before you life and death, blessing and curse. Choose life so that you and your descendants may live,
05Dt 30:20 love the LORD your God, obey Him, and remain faithful to Him. For He is your life, and He will prolong your life in the land the LORD swore to give to your fathers Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob."
05Dt 31:1 Then Moses continued to speak these words to all Israel,
05Dt 31:2 saying, "I am now 120 years old; I can no longer act as your leader. The LORD has told me, 'You will not cross this Jordan.'
05Dt 31:3 The LORD your God is the One who will cross ahead of you. He will destroy these nations before you, and you will drive them out. Joshua is the one who will cross ahead of you, as the LORD has said.
05Dt 31:4 The LORD will deal with them as He did Sihon and Og, the kings of the Amorites, and their land when He destroyed them.
05Dt 31:5 The LORD will deliver them over to you, and you must do to them exactly as I have commanded you.
05Dt 31:6 Be strong and courageous; don't be terrified or afraid of them. For it is the LORD your God who goes with you; He will not leave you or forsake you."
05Dt 31:7 Moses then summoned Joshua and said to him in the sight of all Israel, "Be strong and courageous, for you will go with this people into the land the LORD swore to give to their fathers. You will enable them to take possession of it.
05Dt 31:8 The LORD is the One who will go before you. He will be with you; He will not leave you or forsake you. Do not be afraid or discouraged."
05Dt 31:9 Moses wrote down this law and gave it to the priests, the sons of Levi, who carried the ark of the LORD's covenant, and to all the elders of Israel.
05Dt 31:10 Moses commanded them, "At the end of [every] seven years, at the appointed time in the year of debt cancellation, during the Festival of Booths,
05Dt 31:11 when all Israel assembles in the presence of the LORD your God at the place He chooses, you are to read this law aloud before all Israel.
05Dt 31:12 Gather the people-- men, women, children, and foreigners living within your gates-- so that they may listen and learn to fear the LORD your God and be careful to follow all the words of this law.
05Dt 31:13 Then their children who do not know [the law] will listen and learn to fear the LORD your God as long as you live in the land you are crossing the Jordan to possess."
05Dt 31:14 The LORD said to Moses, "The time of your death is now approaching. Call Joshua and present yourselves at the tent of meeting, so that I may commission him." When Moses and Joshua went and presented themselves at the tent of meeting,
05Dt 31:15 the LORD appeared at the tent in a pillar of cloud, and the cloud stood at the entrance to the tent.
05Dt 31:16 The LORD said to Moses, "You are about to rest with your fathers, and this people will soon commit adultery with the foreign gods of the land they are entering. They will abandon Me and break the covenant I have made with them.
05Dt 31:17 My anger will burn against them on that day; I will abandon them and hide My face from them so that they will become easy prey. Many troubles and afflictions will come to them. On that day they will say, 'Haven't these troubles come to us because our God is no longer with us?'
05Dt 31:18 I will certainly hide My face on that day because of all the evil they have done by turning to other gods.
05Dt 31:19 Therefore write down this song for yourselves and teach it to the Israelites; have them recite it, so that this song may be a witness for Me against the Israelites.
05Dt 31:20 When I bring them into the land I swore to [give] their fathers, [a land] flowing with milk and honey, they will eat their fill and prosper. They will turn to other gods and worship them, despising Me and breaking My covenant.
05Dt 31:21 And when many troubles and afflictions come to them, this song will testify against them, because their descendants will not have forgotten it. For I know what they are prone to do, even before I bring them into the land I swore [to give them]."
05Dt 31:22 So Moses wrote down this song on that day and taught it to the Israelites.
05Dt 31:23 The LORD commissioned Joshua son of Nun, "Be strong and courageous, for you will bring the Israelites into the land I swore to them, and I will be with you."
05Dt 31:24 When Moses had finished writing down on a scroll every single word of this law,
05Dt 31:25 he commanded the Levites who carried the ark of the LORD's covenant,
05Dt 31:26 "Take this book of the law and place it beside the ark of the covenant of the LORD your God, so that it may remain there as a witness against you.
05Dt 31:27 For I know how rebellious and stiff-necked you are. If you are rebelling against the LORD now, while I am still alive, how much more [will you rebel] after I am dead!
05Dt 31:28 Assemble all your tribal elders and officers before me, so that I may speak these words directly to them and call heaven and earth as witnesses against them.
05Dt 31:29 For I know that after my death you will become completely corrupt and turn from the path I have commanded you. Disaster will come to you in the future, because you will do what is evil in the LORD's sight, infuriating Him with what your hands have made."
05Dt 31:30 Then Moses recited aloud every single word of this song to the entire assembly of Israel:
05Dt 32:1 Pay attention, heavens, and I will speak; listen, earth, to the words of my mouth.
05Dt 32:2 Let my teaching fall like rain and my word settle like dew, like gentle rain on new grass and showers on tender plants.
05Dt 32:3 For I will proclaim the LORD's name. Declare the greatness of our God!
05Dt 32:4 The Rock-- His work is perfect; all His ways are entirely just. A faithful God, without prejudice, He is righteous and true.
05Dt 32:5 His people have acted corruptly toward Him; this is their defect-- they are not His children but a devious and crooked generation.
05Dt 32:6 Is this how you repay the LORD, you foolish and senseless people? Isn't He your Father and Creator? Didn't He make you and sustain you?
05Dt 32:7 Remember the days of old; consider the years long past. Ask your father, and he will tell you, your elders, and they will teach you.
05Dt 32:8 When the Most High gave the nations their inheritance and divided the human race, He set the boundaries of the peoples according to the number of the people of Israel.
05Dt 32:9 But the LORD's portion is His people, Jacob, His own inheritance.
05Dt 32:10 He found him in a desolate land, in a barren, howling wilderness; He surrounded him, cared for him, and guarded him as the pupil of His eye.
05Dt 32:11 He watches over His nest like an eagle and hovers over His young; He spreads His wings, catches him, and lifts him up on His pinions.
05Dt 32:12 The LORD alone led him, with no help from a foreign god.
05Dt 32:13 He made him ride on the heights of the land and eat the produce of the field. He nourished him with honey from the rock and oil from flintlike rock,
05Dt 32:14 cream from the herd and milk from the flock, with the fat of lambs, rams from Bashan, and goats, with the choicest grains of wheat; you drank wine from the finest grapes.
05Dt 32:15 Then Jeshurun became fat and rebelled-- you became fat, bloated, and gorged. He abandoned the God who made him and scorned the Rock of his salvation.
05Dt 32:16 They provoked His jealousy with foreign gods; they enraged Him with detestable practices.
05Dt 32:17 They sacrificed to demons, not God, to gods they had not known, new gods that had just arrived, which your fathers did not fear.
05Dt 32:18 You ignored the Rock who gave you birth; you forgot the God who brought you forth.
05Dt 32:19 When the LORD saw [this], He despised [them], provoked [to anger] by His sons and daughters.
05Dt 32:20 He said: "I will hide My face from them; I will see what will become of them, for they are a perverse generation-- unfaithful children.
05Dt 32:21 They have provoked My jealousy with [their] so-called gods; they have enraged Me with their worthless idols. So I will provoke their jealousy with an inferior people; I will enrage them with a foolish nation.
05Dt 32:22 For fire has been kindled because of My anger and burns to the depths of Sheol; it devours the land and its produce, and scorches the foundations of the mountains.
05Dt 32:23 I will pile disasters on them; I will use up My arrows against them.
05Dt 32:24 They will be weak from hunger, ravaged by pestilence and bitter plague; I will unleash on them wild beasts with fangs, as well as venomous snakes that slither in the dust.
05Dt 32:25 Outside, the sword will take their children, and inside, there will be terror; the young man and the virgin [will be killed], the infant and the gray-haired man.
05Dt 32:26 I would have said: I will cut them to pieces and blot out the memory of them from mankind,
05Dt 32:27 if I had not feared insult from the enemy, [or feared] that these foes might misunderstand and say: Our own hand has prevailed; it wasn't the LORD who did all this."
05Dt 32:28 Israel is a nation lacking sense with no understanding at all.
05Dt 32:29 If only they were wise, they would figure it out; they would understand their fate.
05Dt 32:30 How could one man pursue a thousand, or two put ten thousand to flight, unless their Rock had sold them, unless the LORD had given them up?
05Dt 32:31 But their "rock" is not like our Rock; even our enemies concede.
05Dt 32:32 For their vine is from the vine of Sodom and from the fields of Gomorrah. Their grapes are poisonous; their clusters are bitter.
05Dt 32:33 Their wine is serpents' venom, the deadly poison of cobras.
05Dt 32:34 "Is it not stored up with Me, sealed up in My vaults?
05Dt 32:35 Vengeance belongs to Me; I will repay. In time their foot will slip, for their day of disaster is near, and their doom is coming quickly."
05Dt 32:36 The LORD will indeed vindicate His people and have compassion on His servants when He sees that [their] strength is gone and no one is left-- slave or free.
05Dt 32:37 He will say: "Where are their gods, the 'rock' they found refuge in?
05Dt 32:38 Who ate the fat of their sacrifices and drank the wine of their drink offerings? Let them rise up and help you; let it be a shelter for you.
05Dt 32:39 See now that I alone am He; there is no God but Me. I bring death and I give life; I wound and I heal. No one can rescue [anyone] from My hand.
05Dt 32:40 I raise My hand to heaven and declare: As surely as I live forever,
05Dt 32:41 when I sharpen My flashing sword, and My hand takes hold of judgment, I will take vengeance on My adversaries and repay those who hate Me.
05Dt 32:42 I will make My arrows drunk with blood while My sword devours flesh-- the blood of the slain and the captives, the heads of the enemy leaders."
05Dt 32:43 Rejoice, you nations, over His people, for He will avenge the blood of His servants. He will take vengeance on His adversaries; He will purify His land and His people.
05Dt 32:44 Moses came with Joshua son of Nun and recited all the words of this song in the presence of the people.
05Dt 32:45 After Moses finished reciting all these words to all Israel,
05Dt 32:46 he said to them, "Take to heart all these words I am giving as a warning to you today, so that you may command your children to carefully follow all the words of this law.
05Dt 32:47 For they are not meaningless words to you but they are your life, and by them you will live long in the land you are crossing the Jordan to possess."
05Dt 32:48 On that same day the LORD spoke to Moses,
05Dt 32:49 "Go up Mount Nebo in the Abarim [range] in the land of Moab, across from Jericho, and view the land of Canaan I am giving the Israelites as a possession.
05Dt 32:50 Then you will die on the mountain that you go up, and you will be gathered to your people, just as your brother Aaron died on Mount Hor and was gathered to his people.
05Dt 32:51 For [both of] you broke faith with Me among the Israelites at the waters of Meribath-kadesh in the Wilderness of Zin by failing to treat Me as holy in their presence.
05Dt 32:52 Although you will view the land from a distance, which I am giving the Israelites, you will not go there."
05Dt 33:1 This is the blessing that Moses, the man of God, gave the Israelites before his death.
05Dt 33:2 He said: The LORD came from Sinai and appeared to them from Seir; He shone [on them] from Mount Paran and came with ten thousand holy ones, with lightning from His right hand for them.
05Dt 33:3 Indeed He loves the people. All Your holy ones are in Your hand, and they assemble at Your feet. Each receives Your words.
05Dt 33:4 Moses gave us instruction, a possession for the assembly of Jacob.
05Dt 33:5 So He became King in Jeshurun when the leaders of the people gathered with the tribes of Israel.
05Dt 33:6 Let Reuben live and not die though his people become few.
05Dt 33:7 He said this about Judah: LORD, hear Judah's cry and bring him to his people. He fights for his cause with his own hands, but may You be a help against his foes.
05Dt 33:8 He said about Levi: Your Thummim and Urim belong to Your faithful one; You tested him at Massah and contended with him at the waters of Meribah.
05Dt 33:9 He said about his father and mother, "I do not regard them." He disregarded his brothers and didn't acknowledge his sons, for they kept Your word and maintained Your covenant.
05Dt 33:10 They will teach Your ordinances to Jacob and Your instruction to Israel; they will set incense before You and whole burnt offerings on Your altar.
05Dt 33:11 LORD, bless his possessions, and accept the work of his hands. Smash the loins of his adversaries and enemies, so that they cannot rise again.
05Dt 33:12 He said about Benjamin: The LORD's beloved rests securely on Him. He shields him all day long, and he rests on His shoulders.
05Dt 33:13 He said about Joseph: May his land be blessed by the LORD with the dew of heaven's bounty and the watery depths that lie beneath;
05Dt 33:14 with the bountiful harvest from the sun and the abundant yield of the seasons;
05Dt 33:15 with the best products of the ancient mountains and the bounty of the eternal hills;
05Dt 33:16 with the choice gifts of the land and everything in it; and with the favor of Him who appeared in the [burning] bush. May these rest on the head of Joseph, on the crown of the prince of his brothers.
05Dt 33:17 His firstborn bull has splendor, and horns like those of a wild ox; he gores all the peoples with them to the ends of the earth. Such are the ten thousands of Ephraim, and such are the thousands of Manasseh.
05Dt 33:18 He said about Zebulun: Rejoice, Zebulun, in your journeys, and Issachar, in your tents.
05Dt 33:19 They summon the peoples to a mountain; there they offer acceptable sacrifices. For they draw from the wealth of the seas and the hidden treasures of the sand.
05Dt 33:20 He said about Gad: The one who enlarges Gad's [territory] will be blessed. He lies down like a lion and tears off an arm or even a head.
05Dt 33:21 He chose the best [part] for himself, because a ruler's portion was assigned there for him. He came [with] the leaders of the people; he carried out the LORD's justice and His ordinances for Israel.
05Dt 33:22 He said about Dan: Dan is a young lion, leaping out of Bashan.
05Dt 33:23 He said about Naphtali: Naphtali, enjoying approval, full of the LORD's blessing, take possession to the west and the south.
05Dt 33:24 He said about Asher: May Asher be the most blessed of the sons; may he be the most favored among his brothers and dip his foot in [olive] oil.
05Dt 33:25 May the bolts of your gate be iron and bronze, and your strength last as long as you live.
05Dt 33:26 There is none like the God of Jeshurun, who rides the heavens to your aid on the clouds in His majesty.
05Dt 33:27 The God of old is [your] dwelling place, and underneath are the everlasting arms. He drives out the enemy before you, and commands, "Destroy!"
05Dt 33:28 So Israel dwells securely; Jacob lives untroubled in a land of grain and new wine; even his skies drip with dew.
05Dt 33:29 How happy you are, Israel! Who is like you, a people saved by the LORD? He is the shield that protects you, the sword you boast in. Your enemies will cringe before you, and you will tread on their backs.
05Dt 34:1 Then Moses went up from the plains of Moab to Mount Nebo, to the top of Pisgah, which faces Jericho, and the LORD showed him all the land: Gilead as far as Dan,
05Dt 34:2 all of Naphtali, the land of Ephraim and Manasseh, all the land of Judah as far as the Mediterranean Sea,
05Dt 34:3 the Negev, and the region from the Valley of Jericho, the City of Palms, as far as Zoar.
05Dt 34:4 The LORD then said to him, "This is the land I promised Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, 'I will give it to your descendants.' I have let you see it with your own eyes, but you will not cross into it."
05Dt 34:5 So Moses the servant of the LORD died there in the land of Moab, as the LORD had said.
05Dt 34:6 He buried him in the valley in the land of Moab facing Beth-peor, and no one to this day knows where his grave is.
05Dt 34:7 Moses was 120 years old when he died; his eyes were not weak, and his vitality had not left [him].
05Dt 34:8 The Israelites wept for Moses in the plains of Moab 30 days. Then the days of weeping and mourning for Moses came to an end.
05Dt 34:9 Joshua son of Nun was filled with the spirit of wisdom, because Moses had laid his hands on him. So the Israelites obeyed him and did as the LORD had commanded Moses.
05Dt 34:10 No prophet has arisen again in Israel like Moses, whom the LORD knew face to face.
05Dt 34:11 [He was unparalleled] for all the signs and wonders the LORD sent him to do against the land of Egypt-- to Pharaoh, to all his officials, and to all his land,
05Dt 34:12 and for all the mighty [acts of] power and terrifying deeds that Moses performed in the sight of all Israel.
